WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:02.475 align:middle line:90%
[WHOOSH]

00:00:02.475 --> 00:00:04.950 align:middle line:90%


00:00:04.950 --> 00:00:08.910 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:00:08.910 --> 00:00:12.890 align:middle line:90%


00:00:12.890 --> 00:00:16.790 align:middle line:84%
>> As a filmmaker, I try to
remain a neutral observer,

00:00:16.790 --> 00:00:20.390 align:middle line:84%
but what caused me to tell Stan
Grof's story and what I learned

00:00:20.390 --> 00:00:23.240 align:middle line:84%
in the process made
that impossible.

00:00:23.240 --> 00:00:25.820 align:middle line:90%


00:00:25.820 --> 00:00:27.170 align:middle line:90%
My name is Susan.

00:00:27.170 --> 00:00:29.900 align:middle line:84%
And for most of my life,
I felt like I really

00:00:29.900 --> 00:00:34.060 align:middle line:84%
didn't belong here, like I
was born on the wrong planet.

00:00:34.060 --> 00:00:36.660 align:middle line:90%


00:00:36.660 --> 00:00:39.240 align:middle line:84%
All I could think of
was how to go back.

00:00:39.240 --> 00:00:42.952 align:middle line:90%
[BABY CRYING]

00:00:42.952 --> 00:00:44.810 align:middle line:90%


00:00:44.810 --> 00:00:47.990 align:middle line:84%
The magic that filled
my dreams would

00:00:47.990 --> 00:00:50.560 align:middle line:90%
evaporate with the daylight.

00:00:50.560 --> 00:00:54.310 align:middle line:84%
For a while, ballet seemed like
the place where I belonged,

00:00:54.310 --> 00:00:55.960 align:middle line:84%
but even that
eventually changed.

00:00:55.960 --> 00:00:58.500 align:middle line:90%


00:00:58.500 --> 00:01:01.460 align:middle line:84%
Then in my early
20s, I tried LSD.

00:01:01.460 --> 00:01:02.850 align:middle line:90%
[CHEERING]

00:01:02.850 --> 00:01:06.980 align:middle line:84%
For the first time,
I felt lovable.

00:01:06.980 --> 00:01:11.920 align:middle line:84%
Finally, I believed in myself,
and everything changed.

00:01:11.920 --> 00:01:14.370 align:middle line:84%
But without a
structure to ground me,

00:01:14.370 --> 00:01:18.240 align:middle line:84%
I made bad choices that
harmed my body and others that

00:01:18.240 --> 00:01:21.820 align:middle line:90%
took years to undo.

00:01:21.820 --> 00:01:26.360 align:middle line:84%
And then I discovered shamanism
and learned how to journey.

00:01:26.360 --> 00:01:31.570 align:middle line:84%
Up I went, past the clouds,
beyond the Earth's atmosphere

00:01:31.570 --> 00:01:35.520 align:middle line:84%
until I was surrounded
by darkness.

00:01:35.520 --> 00:01:39.690 align:middle line:84%
I met my teachers and felt
that I had known them forever.

00:01:39.690 --> 00:01:42.870 align:middle line:84%
They healed me, helped me
make sense of the world,

00:01:42.870 --> 00:01:46.030 align:middle line:90%
and could explain anything.

00:01:46.030 --> 00:01:48.970 align:middle line:84%
Once I even asked for a
story, and they showed me one.

00:01:48.970 --> 00:02:03.820 align:middle line:90%


00:02:03.820 --> 00:02:10.280 align:middle line:84%
I started to make changes
that were difficult.

00:02:10.280 --> 00:02:14.180 align:middle line:84%
I traveled to France
and fell in love.

00:02:14.180 --> 00:02:15.950 align:middle line:84%
But then we couldn't
get pregnant,

00:02:15.950 --> 00:02:18.800 align:middle line:84%
and I learned that
if I wanted a baby,

00:02:18.800 --> 00:02:20.420 align:middle line:84%
I'd have to tune
back into Earth.

00:02:20.420 --> 00:02:31.222 align:middle line:90%


00:02:31.222 --> 00:02:34.670 align:middle line:10%
>> We got a lot of candy.

00:02:34.670 --> 00:02:38.700 align:middle line:84%
When I thought my kids were old
enough, I tried to reconnect.

00:02:38.700 --> 00:02:41.060 align:middle line:84%
There were insights,
but no upward journey

00:02:41.060 --> 00:02:42.980 align:middle line:90%
to meet my teachers.

00:02:42.980 --> 00:02:45.800 align:middle line:84%
In the search for another
way to reconnect with them,

00:02:45.800 --> 00:02:48.050 align:middle line:90%
I learned about Stan Grof.

00:02:48.050 --> 00:02:50.330 align:middle line:84%
>> Consciousness is not
something that emerges

00:02:50.330 --> 00:02:54.530 align:middle line:84%
as an accident after billions
of years of evolution,

00:02:54.530 --> 00:02:57.120 align:middle line:84%
something that requires
a central nervous system.

00:02:57.120 --> 00:03:00.950 align:middle line:84%
And I had an experience that
just literally changed my life,

00:03:00.950 --> 00:03:03.500 align:middle line:84%
both professionally
and personally.

00:03:03.500 --> 00:03:08.180 align:middle line:84%
People get tranquilizers
and get hospitalized

00:03:08.180 --> 00:03:10.550 align:middle line:84%
for experiences that
in other cultures

00:03:10.550 --> 00:03:14.340 align:middle line:84%
would be considered
extremely valuable.

00:03:14.340 --> 00:03:17.760 align:middle line:84%
>> Stan Grof is known as
a pioneer of psychedelic

00:03:17.760 --> 00:03:21.750 align:middle line:84%
psychotherapy, drawing from
his own experiences and from

00:03:21.750 --> 00:03:26.590 align:middle line:84%
thousands of high-dose LSD
sessions with his patients.

00:03:26.590 --> 00:03:28.510 align:middle line:84%
The insights he
gained personally

00:03:28.510 --> 00:03:31.240 align:middle line:84%
combined with the
experiences of his patients

00:03:31.240 --> 00:03:36.150 align:middle line:84%
expanded his understanding
of the human psyche.

00:03:36.150 --> 00:03:38.760 align:middle line:84%
It stretched beyond the
biographical information

00:03:38.760 --> 00:03:43.470 align:middle line:84%
that begins after we are
born to memories surrounding

00:03:43.470 --> 00:03:46.335 align:middle line:84%
our time in the womb and
during the birth process.

00:03:46.335 --> 00:03:49.560 align:middle line:90%


00:03:49.560 --> 00:03:52.710 align:middle line:84%
His expanded map even
included the spiritual nature

00:03:52.710 --> 00:03:56.940 align:middle line:84%
of humanity, recognizing
past life experiences

00:03:56.940 --> 00:04:00.495 align:middle line:84%
and dimensions of consciousness
we share with all of creation.

00:04:00.495 --> 00:04:03.220 align:middle line:90%


00:04:03.220 --> 00:04:06.130 align:middle line:10%
Stan used these insights
to co-found transpersonal

00:04:06.130 --> 00:04:09.790 align:middle line:10%
psychology with Abraham Maslow,
and working with his wife

00:04:09.790 --> 00:04:12.790 align:middle line:10%
Christina, organized
international transpersonal

00:04:12.790 --> 00:04:14.410 align:middle line:10%
conferences around the world.

00:04:14.410 --> 00:04:19.220 align:middle line:90%


00:04:19.220 --> 00:04:21.680 align:middle line:10%
During much of this
period, Stan was also

00:04:21.680 --> 00:04:25.490 align:middle line:10%
the scholar in residence at the
Esalen Institute in Big Sur.

00:04:25.490 --> 00:04:29.000 align:middle line:10%
Spiritual masters and
groundbreaking pioneers

00:04:29.000 --> 00:04:31.910 align:middle line:10%
representing a broad
spectrum of disciplines

00:04:31.910 --> 00:04:34.220 align:middle line:10%
were frequent guests
at the workshops

00:04:34.220 --> 00:04:37.400 align:middle line:10%
and month-long retreats he
offered during his 14 years

00:04:37.400 --> 00:04:38.900 align:middle line:10%
there.

00:04:38.900 --> 00:04:41.420 align:middle line:84%
It was there that Stan
and Christina developed

00:04:41.420 --> 00:04:44.390 align:middle line:84%
holotropic breathwork, a
breathing technique that

00:04:44.390 --> 00:04:46.670 align:middle line:84%
could induce powerful
non-ordinary states

00:04:46.670 --> 00:04:52.040 align:middle line:84%
of consciousness, similar
to an LSD session.

00:04:52.040 --> 00:04:53.630 align:middle line:90%
I had to meet Stan.

00:04:53.630 --> 00:04:57.830 align:middle line:84%
On some deep level, I knew he
could help me find my way back

00:04:57.830 --> 00:05:00.230 align:middle line:90%
in.

00:05:00.230 --> 00:05:02.660 align:middle line:84%
When I learned he would
be teaching a course,

00:05:02.660 --> 00:05:06.600 align:middle line:90%
I signed up immediately.

00:05:06.600 --> 00:05:09.000 align:middle line:10%
>> We're so far talking
about non-ordinary states

00:05:09.000 --> 00:05:13.230 align:middle line:10%
of consciousness, but I have
been all these 60 years now

00:05:13.230 --> 00:05:15.720 align:middle line:10%
interested in a
very significant,

00:05:15.720 --> 00:05:20.700 align:middle line:10%
large subgroup of these
non-ordinary experiences

00:05:20.700 --> 00:05:25.730 align:middle line:10%
for which current psychiatry and
psychology has no special name.

00:05:25.730 --> 00:05:28.380 align:middle line:84%
They are all put in the
category of altered states

00:05:28.380 --> 00:05:29.610 align:middle line:90%
of consciousness.

00:05:29.610 --> 00:05:32.430 align:middle line:84%
What it suggests
somehow is that there's

00:05:32.430 --> 00:05:35.490 align:middle line:84%
a correct way of experiencing
ourselves and the world,

00:05:35.490 --> 00:05:38.770 align:middle line:84%
and that in these
states, it's distorted.

00:05:38.770 --> 00:05:41.250 align:middle line:10%
We have to use
this new psychology

00:05:41.250 --> 00:05:44.940 align:middle line:10%
if we want to use effectively
holotropic states,

00:05:44.940 --> 00:05:47.295 align:middle line:10%
if you want to run
psychedelic sessions

00:05:47.295 --> 00:05:51.230 align:middle line:10%
or do holotropic
breathwork or if we

00:05:51.230 --> 00:05:54.800 align:middle line:10%
want to work with people who
are in spiritual emergency.

00:05:54.800 --> 00:05:57.710 align:middle line:84%
>> I had read about Stan's
theories on how our experiences

00:05:57.710 --> 00:05:59.930 align:middle line:84%
in the womb affected
our unconscious,

00:05:59.930 --> 00:06:04.460 align:middle line:84%
but to hear him explain it gave
me a whole new understanding.

00:06:04.460 --> 00:06:07.940 align:middle line:84%
>> The experiences-- if
you regress to birth,

00:06:07.940 --> 00:06:10.700 align:middle line:84%
the experiences come
in four patterns.

00:06:10.700 --> 00:06:16.280 align:middle line:10%
I call them perinatal matrices,
basic perinatal matrices.

00:06:16.280 --> 00:06:18.980 align:middle line:84%
The first perinatal
matrix relates

00:06:18.980 --> 00:06:21.800 align:middle line:84%
to the situation
of the fetus still

00:06:21.800 --> 00:06:26.210 align:middle line:84%
in the womb before the
onset of the delivery.

00:06:26.210 --> 00:06:30.650 align:middle line:84%
This could be pregnancy which
is the result of planning,

00:06:30.650 --> 00:06:33.830 align:middle line:84%
of the parents'
loving expectation.

00:06:33.830 --> 00:06:35.780 align:middle line:84%
The mother is
physically healthy, is

00:06:35.780 --> 00:06:39.270 align:middle line:90%
in emotionally good condition.

00:06:39.270 --> 00:06:41.900 align:middle line:84%
A reliving of that
kind of state would

00:06:41.900 --> 00:06:45.500 align:middle line:90%
be a very ecstatic experience.

00:06:45.500 --> 00:06:48.390 align:middle line:84%
Now, this doesn't
necessarily happen.

00:06:48.390 --> 00:06:51.140 align:middle line:84%
There are pregnancies
which are a result of rape,

00:06:51.140 --> 00:06:55.220 align:middle line:84%
of a one-night stand when
both parents were drunk,

00:06:55.220 --> 00:06:58.070 align:middle line:84%
where the marriage
was broken, the mother

00:06:58.070 --> 00:07:03.260 align:middle line:84%
is abused, physically and
emotionally unhealthy.

00:07:03.260 --> 00:07:05.540 align:middle line:84%
The pregnancy could
be so unwelcome

00:07:05.540 --> 00:07:09.080 align:middle line:84%
that there are
attempts at abortion.

00:07:09.080 --> 00:07:12.830 align:middle line:84%
Another possibility, the
mother is Rh negative,

00:07:12.830 --> 00:07:16.490 align:middle line:84%
the father is Rh positive
so that from the beginning,

00:07:16.490 --> 00:07:20.360 align:middle line:84%
the fetus is being attacked,
immunologically treated

00:07:20.360 --> 00:07:22.280 align:middle line:90%
as an invader.

00:07:22.280 --> 00:07:24.740 align:middle line:84%
Come nine months
plus minus, this

00:07:24.740 --> 00:07:27.650 align:middle line:90%
is the onset of the delivery.

00:07:27.650 --> 00:07:29.960 align:middle line:84%
First, hormonal
changes, which are then

00:07:29.960 --> 00:07:35.230 align:middle line:84%
translated into mechanical
contractions of the uterus.

00:07:35.230 --> 00:07:38.990 align:middle line:84%
Each contraction compresses
the arteries and interrupts

00:07:38.990 --> 00:07:43.830 align:middle line:84%
placentary circulation between
the mother and the child,

00:07:43.830 --> 00:07:47.810 align:middle line:84%
which means no supply of oxygen,
no nourishment coming in,

00:07:47.810 --> 00:07:52.040 align:middle line:84%
and there's no removal
of metabolic product.

00:07:52.040 --> 00:07:55.310 align:middle line:84%
There's no resolution for it
because the cervix is not open.

00:07:55.310 --> 00:08:00.710 align:middle line:84%
Just contractions of the
uterus in a closed system.

00:08:00.710 --> 00:08:03.070 align:middle line:10%
Now with each
contraction, the cervix

00:08:03.070 --> 00:08:04.630 align:middle line:10%
is being pulled over the head.

00:08:04.630 --> 00:08:06.190 align:middle line:90%
It's dilating.

00:08:06.190 --> 00:08:08.800 align:middle line:84%
When it reaches
the necessary size,

00:08:08.800 --> 00:08:14.170 align:middle line:84%
then it's the transition
to the third matrix.

00:08:14.170 --> 00:08:17.170 align:middle line:84%
The contractions continue
with all the consequences,

00:08:17.170 --> 00:08:19.870 align:middle line:84%
but the cervix is
now open, so there

00:08:19.870 --> 00:08:23.800 align:middle line:84%
is these laborious propulsions
through the birth canal.

00:08:23.800 --> 00:08:26.590 align:middle line:84%
Now there are tremendous
pressures here.

00:08:26.590 --> 00:08:30.700 align:middle line:84%
Suffocation and the pain
generate powerful energy,

00:08:30.700 --> 00:08:35.110 align:middle line:84%
which has all the
qualities of sexual energy.

00:08:35.110 --> 00:08:37.690 align:middle line:84%
Our first encounter
with sexual energy,

00:08:37.690 --> 00:08:40.400 align:middle line:84%
we were inflicting pain
on another organism.

00:08:40.400 --> 00:08:44.540 align:middle line:84%
Another organism was
inflicting pain on us.

00:08:44.540 --> 00:08:46.400 align:middle line:90%
We couldn't breathe.

00:08:46.400 --> 00:08:50.210 align:middle line:84%
There were a lot of
pressures and fear.

00:08:50.210 --> 00:08:53.480 align:middle line:84%
This kind of experience
then can become the basis

00:08:53.480 --> 00:08:56.480 align:middle line:84%
of the development of
various sexual dysfunctions,

00:08:56.480 --> 00:09:01.410 align:middle line:84%
deviations, aberrations,
perversions.

00:09:01.410 --> 00:09:04.760 align:middle line:84%
Then we have the completion
of the delivery, head first

00:09:04.760 --> 00:09:06.920 align:middle line:90%
or feet first.

00:09:06.920 --> 00:09:09.710 align:middle line:84%
And then the
umbilical cord is cut.

00:09:09.710 --> 00:09:14.180 align:middle line:84%
From then on, the child exists
as an anatomically independent

00:09:14.180 --> 00:09:17.760 align:middle line:84%
individual, still biologically,
emotionally dependent,

00:09:17.760 --> 00:09:18.560 align:middle line:90%
of course.

00:09:18.560 --> 00:09:24.880 align:middle line:90%


00:09:24.880 --> 00:09:28.580 align:middle line:84%
>> The matrices
begin with unity,

00:09:28.580 --> 00:09:32.820 align:middle line:84%
transition to hell
with no escape,

00:09:32.820 --> 00:09:36.540 align:middle line:84%
then to purgatory with the
end in sight where you are

00:09:36.540 --> 00:09:40.470 align:middle line:84%
the victim and the
perpetrator and the observer,

00:09:40.470 --> 00:09:44.580 align:middle line:84%
and finally culminate in
freedom and a newfound sense

00:09:44.580 --> 00:09:45.744 align:middle line:90%
of connection.

00:09:45.744 --> 00:09:49.540 align:middle line:90%


00:09:49.540 --> 00:09:52.780 align:middle line:84%
As Stan finished, I remembered
the rebirthing workshop

00:09:52.780 --> 00:09:55.840 align:middle line:84%
I'd taken at Rajneeshpuram
back in the '80s.

00:09:55.840 --> 00:09:58.990 align:middle line:84%
I felt like I was dropping
into a deep pit that grew

00:09:58.990 --> 00:10:02.130 align:middle line:90%
more painful as I descended.

00:10:02.130 --> 00:10:05.100 align:middle line:84%
Just when I thought
I was going to die,

00:10:05.100 --> 00:10:07.790 align:middle line:84%
I burst through into an
ocean of love and light.

00:10:07.790 --> 00:10:20.350 align:middle line:90%


00:10:20.350 --> 00:10:23.050 align:middle line:84%
Joseph Campbell is
best known for his work

00:10:23.050 --> 00:10:25.300 align:middle line:84%
in comparing mythologies
and religions

00:10:25.300 --> 00:10:28.180 align:middle line:90%
from cultures around the world.

00:10:28.180 --> 00:10:32.440 align:middle line:84%
He met Stan in the late '60s at
a conference in New York City.

00:10:32.440 --> 00:10:33.970 align:middle line:84%
When Campbell
heard Stan's theory

00:10:33.970 --> 00:10:36.790 align:middle line:84%
on the four perinatal
matrices, he instantly

00:10:36.790 --> 00:10:40.480 align:middle line:84%
solved a mystery that had
intrigued him for years.

00:10:40.480 --> 00:10:42.220 align:middle line:10%
He couldn't understand
how cultures

00:10:42.220 --> 00:10:44.530 align:middle line:10%
from diverse
geographical locations

00:10:44.530 --> 00:10:47.440 align:middle line:10%
could share the same
death rebirth themes.

00:10:47.440 --> 00:10:50.260 align:middle line:90%
He called it a monomyth.

00:10:50.260 --> 00:10:52.720 align:middle line:84%
But when he saw
Stan's presentation,

00:10:52.720 --> 00:10:54.730 align:middle line:84%
he understood that
these cultures

00:10:54.730 --> 00:10:57.760 align:middle line:84%
were reliving the experience
of their own birth.

00:10:57.760 --> 00:11:00.730 align:middle line:84%
The perinatal matrices,
especially the third

00:11:00.730 --> 00:11:03.670 align:middle line:84%
moving into the fourth,
served as the threshold

00:11:03.670 --> 00:11:05.860 align:middle line:90%
for the hero's journey.

00:11:05.860 --> 00:11:08.650 align:middle line:84%
The rites of passage that
these cultures developed

00:11:08.650 --> 00:11:11.860 align:middle line:84%
allowed their initiates to
access unconscious birth

00:11:11.860 --> 00:11:14.380 align:middle line:84%
memories, face
their fear of death,

00:11:14.380 --> 00:11:18.490 align:middle line:84%
and finally free themselves
from a deep maternal dependency.

00:11:18.490 --> 00:11:22.510 align:middle line:90%


00:11:22.510 --> 00:11:25.360 align:middle line:84%
>> Birth itself is not
only a rite of passage,

00:11:25.360 --> 00:11:30.340 align:middle line:84%
but is perhaps the universal
rite of passage that we all go

00:11:30.340 --> 00:11:31.450 align:middle line:90%
through.

00:11:31.450 --> 00:11:34.120 align:middle line:84%
Perhaps it's through
that experience

00:11:34.120 --> 00:11:37.510 align:middle line:84%
that we come into the
world, knowing deeply

00:11:37.510 --> 00:11:42.100 align:middle line:84%
that if we are to succeed
in the ongoing actualization

00:11:42.100 --> 00:11:43.720 align:middle line:84%
of our potentials,
whatever they are

00:11:43.720 --> 00:11:46.330 align:middle line:84%
as individuals,
throughout the life cycle,

00:11:46.330 --> 00:11:50.800 align:middle line:84%
for however long we live, we
will need to undergo repeatedly

00:11:50.800 --> 00:11:52.270 align:middle line:90%
similar rites of passage.

00:11:52.270 --> 00:11:55.230 align:middle line:90%


00:11:55.230 --> 00:11:57.450 align:middle line:84%
>> Holotropic breathwork
is an experiential approach

00:11:57.450 --> 00:12:01.420 align:middle line:84%
to self-exploration, to
therapy which uses very,

00:12:01.420 --> 00:12:02.580 align:middle line:90%
very simple means.

00:12:02.580 --> 00:12:04.620 align:middle line:90%
It uses faster breathing.

00:12:04.620 --> 00:12:08.310 align:middle line:84%
It uses powerful, evocative
music, and also a certain kind

00:12:08.310 --> 00:12:10.110 align:middle line:90%
of bodywork when it's indicated.

00:12:10.110 --> 00:12:13.350 align:middle line:90%


00:12:13.350 --> 00:12:16.060 align:middle line:84%
>> So each individual
will choose a partner.

00:12:16.060 --> 00:12:19.710 align:middle line:10%
One of those people does the
breathing and the other person

00:12:19.710 --> 00:12:23.170 align:middle line:10%
sits with him or her, and
then they switch roles

00:12:23.170 --> 00:12:25.860 align:middle line:10%
so that everybody gets
a chance to participate

00:12:25.860 --> 00:12:29.160 align:middle line:10%
both as a breather and
as what we call a sitter.

00:12:29.160 --> 00:12:32.190 align:middle line:10%
>> And we also combine it with
what we call mandala drawings.

00:12:32.190 --> 00:12:34.650 align:middle line:84%
And after the session,
