were strong enough

00:24:36.220 --> 00:24:39.610 align:middle line:84%
to cause broken bones if the
patients weren't restrained.

00:24:39.610 --> 00:24:42.610 align:middle line:84%
Curare derived from
South American plants

00:24:42.610 --> 00:24:45.040 align:middle line:84%
was later used to
paralyze motor nerves

00:24:45.040 --> 00:24:46.810 align:middle line:90%
and lessen the convulsions.

00:24:46.810 --> 00:24:51.880 align:middle line:84%
Stan administered 25
electroshock convulsions daily.

00:24:51.880 --> 00:24:55.810 align:middle line:84%
Even psychoanalysis proved
disappointing for Stan.

00:24:55.810 --> 00:24:59.320 align:middle line:84%
>> I mean, I was in
psychoanalysis for seven years.

00:24:59.320 --> 00:25:03.170 align:middle line:84%
And when in the fourth year I
started bringing in my dreams

00:25:03.170 --> 00:25:05.830 align:middle line:84%
images that were related
to the [INAUDIBLE],,

00:25:05.830 --> 00:25:10.210 align:middle line:84%
this was considered to
be relatively successful

00:25:10.210 --> 00:25:11.950 align:middle line:90%
psychoanalysis.

00:25:11.950 --> 00:25:15.460 align:middle line:10%
>> Fortunately for Stan,
Sandoz Laboratories needed help

00:25:15.460 --> 00:25:19.210 align:middle line:10%
exploring applications for a
new drug synthesized by Albert

00:25:19.210 --> 00:25:24.040 align:middle line:10%
Hoffman, Lysergic Acid
Diethylamide, or LSD.

00:25:24.040 --> 00:25:26.800 align:middle line:84%
The Swiss scientist was
revisiting his synthesis

00:25:26.800 --> 00:25:29.440 align:middle line:84%
of the ergot fungus
when he accidentally

00:25:29.440 --> 00:25:30.940 align:middle line:90%
intoxicated himself.

00:25:30.940 --> 00:25:33.790 align:middle line:84%
A drop of the clear
solution touched his finger

00:25:33.790 --> 00:25:36.880 align:middle line:84%
and was absorbed into his
system when he wiped his eye.

00:25:36.880 --> 00:25:39.520 align:middle line:84%
Intrigued by the
unusual sensations,

00:25:39.520 --> 00:25:41.800 align:middle line:84%
Hoffman decided to
try a tiny dose.

00:25:41.800 --> 00:25:45.520 align:middle line:84%
A few days later, what followed
was an endless bike ride

00:25:45.520 --> 00:25:48.220 align:middle line:84%
home and a call for
a doctor when Hoffman

00:25:48.220 --> 00:25:49.720 align:middle line:90%
thought he might be dying.

00:25:49.720 --> 00:25:52.540 align:middle line:84%
Once the crisis passed,
Hoffman realized

00:25:52.540 --> 00:25:55.600 align:middle line:84%
that his discovery was
an incredibly powerful

00:25:55.600 --> 00:25:58.120 align:middle line:90%
psychotropic substance.

00:25:58.120 --> 00:26:05.050 align:middle line:84%
>> In 1954, we got a
sample of ampules of LSD.

00:26:05.050 --> 00:26:06.820 align:middle line:84%
They got an idea
that it might be

00:26:06.820 --> 00:26:11.290 align:middle line:84%
something interesting for
psychiatrists, psychologists.

00:26:11.290 --> 00:26:14.420 align:middle line:84%
And would we want
to work with it?

00:26:14.420 --> 00:26:16.930 align:middle line:84%
So my preceptor did
not have the time

00:26:16.930 --> 00:26:21.510 align:middle line:84%
to spend six to eight
hours with people on LSD.

00:26:21.510 --> 00:26:25.075 align:middle line:84%
And so he used several
of us as gophers.

00:26:25.075 --> 00:26:27.880 align:middle line:84%
We were sitting
there and taking care

00:26:27.880 --> 00:26:32.170 align:middle line:84%
of the experimental subjects
and keeping records.

00:26:32.170 --> 00:26:35.420 align:middle line:84%
But in that early stage,
students were excluded.

00:26:35.420 --> 00:26:37.960 align:middle line:84%
So I had two years
when I was listening

00:26:37.960 --> 00:26:40.240 align:middle line:84%
to these incredible
stories and not being

00:26:40.240 --> 00:26:41.890 align:middle line:90%
able to have the experience.

00:26:41.890 --> 00:26:43.650 align:middle line:84%
So just about the
first thing I did

00:26:43.650 --> 00:26:48.640 align:middle line:84%
when I graduated was to
have this experience myself.

00:26:48.640 --> 00:26:51.610 align:middle line:84%
My teacher was specifically
interested in training

00:26:51.610 --> 00:26:54.310 align:middle line:84%
the brainwaves, which
means exposing people

00:26:54.310 --> 00:26:57.610 align:middle line:84%
to powerful stroboscopic
light of various frequencies

00:26:57.610 --> 00:27:01.300 align:middle line:84%
and finding out if you can
influence the brainwaves

00:27:01.300 --> 00:27:03.160 align:middle line:90%
in the suboccipital area.

00:27:03.160 --> 00:27:06.070 align:middle line:84%
So those of us who
wanted to have a session,

00:27:06.070 --> 00:27:08.920 align:middle line:84%
we had to agree that
we also would be

00:27:08.920 --> 00:27:11.500 align:middle line:90%
going through this experiment.

00:27:11.500 --> 00:27:14.500 align:middle line:84%
When my own experience
was culminating,

00:27:14.500 --> 00:27:18.400 align:middle line:84%
a research assistant took
me to a very little room,

00:27:18.400 --> 00:27:21.670 align:middle line:84%
and then she brought
this gigantic strobe.

00:27:21.670 --> 00:27:23.380 align:middle line:84%
And in the next
moment, there was light

00:27:23.380 --> 00:27:26.860 align:middle line:84%
like I had never
seen in my life.

00:27:26.860 --> 00:27:31.060 align:middle line:84%
My consciousness was
catapulted out of my body.

00:27:31.060 --> 00:27:34.000 align:middle line:90%
I lost the research assistant.

00:27:34.000 --> 00:27:34.960 align:middle line:90%
I lost the clinic.

00:27:34.960 --> 00:27:35.890 align:middle line:90%
I lost Prague.

00:27:35.890 --> 00:27:38.470 align:middle line:90%
I lost the planet.

00:27:38.470 --> 00:27:42.190 align:middle line:84%
Then I had the feeling that I
was completely extinguished.

00:27:42.190 --> 00:27:47.470 align:middle line:84%
I ceased to exist in the
form in which I knew myself.

00:27:47.470 --> 00:27:49.570 align:middle line:84%
And instead, I had the
feeling that I somehow

00:27:49.570 --> 00:27:52.440 align:middle line:90%
became all of existence.

00:27:52.440 --> 00:27:55.360 align:middle line:84%
I became nothing, but
if I became nothing,

00:27:55.360 --> 00:27:57.546 align:middle line:90%
I became everything.

00:27:57.546 --> 00:28:01.280 align:middle line:90%


00:28:01.280 --> 00:28:03.665 align:middle line:84%
I was in the
astronomical universe,

00:28:03.665 --> 00:28:07.040 align:middle line:90%
or I was the universe.

00:28:07.040 --> 00:28:09.540 align:middle line:84%
And there are things happening
for which at the time

00:28:09.540 --> 00:28:11.210 align:middle line:90%
I didn't even have a name.

00:28:11.210 --> 00:28:13.190 align:middle line:84%
But later, I read
about the Big Bang

00:28:13.190 --> 00:28:16.200 align:middle line:84%
and the black holes and the
white holes and wormholes.

00:28:16.200 --> 00:28:19.850 align:middle line:84%
It was just an amazing
cosmic spectacle.

00:28:19.850 --> 00:28:22.870 align:middle line:90%


00:28:22.870 --> 00:28:24.620 align:middle line:90%
And then she turned it off.

00:28:24.620 --> 00:28:27.130 align:middle line:84%
My consciousness
started shrinking again.

00:28:27.130 --> 00:28:29.290 align:middle line:90%
I became myself.

00:28:29.290 --> 00:28:32.560 align:middle line:84%
But there was a problem, because
I ended up finding the planet,

00:28:32.560 --> 00:28:34.480 align:middle line:84%
finding the clinic,
finding my body.

00:28:34.480 --> 00:28:37.870 align:middle line:84%
But my consciousness was kind
of floating around the body,

00:28:37.870 --> 00:28:42.380 align:middle line:84%
and I couldn't find ways
of aligning those two.

00:28:42.380 --> 00:28:44.570 align:middle line:84%
At that point, it was
absolutely clear to me

00:28:44.570 --> 00:28:46.440 align:middle line:84%
that what they taught
me at the university,

00:28:46.440 --> 00:28:49.400 align:middle line:84%
that consciousness
is somehow created

00:28:49.400 --> 00:28:53.270 align:middle line:84%
by the activity of the
neurons in the brain, suddenly

00:28:53.270 --> 00:28:55.180 align:middle line:90%
it's totally absurd.

00:28:55.180 --> 00:28:56.740 align:middle line:84%
It was clear to me
that consciousness

00:28:56.740 --> 00:28:59.350 align:middle line:90%
was a cosmic phenomenon.

00:28:59.350 --> 00:29:03.400 align:middle line:84%
Could matter bouncing off
atoms or subatomic particles

00:29:03.400 --> 00:29:07.570 align:middle line:84%
create all that we see,
including the beauty of nature,

00:29:07.570 --> 00:29:11.380 align:middle line:84%
the beauty of the universe,
the intelligence that you

00:29:11.380 --> 00:29:13.480 align:middle line:84%
see in animals, that
you see in people?

00:29:13.480 --> 00:29:18.970 align:middle line:84%
Is it really something that can
create science and philosophy?

00:29:18.970 --> 00:29:20.830 align:middle line:90%
When you see it, it's absurd.

00:29:20.830 --> 00:29:23.905 align:middle line:84%
There is a beauty and there is
an intelligence which cannot

00:29:23.905 --> 00:29:25.120 align:middle line:90%
come out of matter.

00:29:25.120 --> 00:29:30.880 align:middle line:90%


00:29:30.880 --> 00:29:33.490 align:middle line:84%
Then I came down
from this session.

00:29:33.490 --> 00:29:35.730 align:middle line:84%
But if I'm now stuck
with psychiatry,

00:29:35.730 --> 00:29:38.020 align:middle line:84%
this is by far the
most interesting thing

00:29:38.020 --> 00:29:40.900 align:middle line:84%
I could do, studying
these non-ordinary states.

00:29:40.900 --> 00:29:44.350 align:middle line:90%


00:29:44.350 --> 00:29:47.110 align:middle line:84%
>> At a complex of research
institutes near Prague,

00:29:47.110 --> 00:29:51.100 align:middle line:84%
Stan was involved in laboratory
testing of LSD and other

00:29:51.100 --> 00:29:54.340 align:middle line:84%
substances such as
psilocybin and mescaline.

00:29:54.340 --> 00:29:57.490 align:middle line:84%
40 test subjects, a mix
of healthy individuals

00:29:57.490 --> 00:30:01.180 align:middle line:84%
and psychiatric patients, would
undergo hourly blood draws,

00:30:01.180 --> 00:30:04.900 align:middle line:84%
urine samples, and psychological
and neurological testing

00:30:04.900 --> 00:30:07.540 align:middle line:84%
during their sessions,
all in the hope

00:30:07.540 --> 00:30:12.870 align:middle line:84%
of identifying the chemical
source of mental illness.

00:30:12.870 --> 00:30:16.820 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, the initial excitement
was that LSD can produce what

00:30:16.820 --> 00:30:19.250 align:middle line:84%
we called experimental
psychosis.

00:30:19.250 --> 00:30:21.930 align:middle line:84%
We can give it to quote,
unquote, "normal people."

00:30:21.930 --> 00:30:24.840 align:middle line:84%
We can do all kinds of tests
before, during, and after.

00:30:24.840 --> 00:30:28.100 align:middle line:84%
And we get an idea of what's
happening biochemically

00:30:28.100 --> 00:30:31.130 align:middle line:84%
when the cycle is so
profoundly influenced.

00:30:31.130 --> 00:30:33.650 align:middle line:84%
And this was fascinating,
because we are talking

00:30:33.650 --> 00:30:38.210 align:middle line:90%
about microscopic amounts.

00:30:38.210 --> 00:30:41.000 align:middle line:84%
Hundred millions of
a gram can change

00:30:41.000 --> 00:30:46.070 align:middle line:84%
profoundly human consciousness
for six to eight hours.

00:30:46.070 --> 00:30:48.320 align:middle line:84%
If this is the case,
mental diseases,

00:30:48.320 --> 00:30:51.150 align:middle line:84%
it would be aberrations
of chemistry.

00:30:51.150 --> 00:30:54.470 align:middle line:84%
Now if we could identify
this chemical culprit,

00:30:54.470 --> 00:30:58.370 align:middle line:84%
we could also find some
kind of neutralizing agent.

00:30:58.370 --> 00:31:02.630 align:middle line:84%
And this would have been my test
tube solution of schizophrenia

00:31:02.630 --> 00:31:04.730 align:middle line:90%
and other psychosis.

00:31:04.730 --> 00:31:09.950 align:middle line:84%
This would be like the
Holy Grail of psychiatry.

00:31:09.950 --> 00:31:13.070 align:middle line:84%
>> But during the testing,
it became clear that it was

00:31:13.070 --> 00:31:16.490 align:middle line:84%
impossible to predict the kind
of experience subjects would

00:31:16.490 --> 00:31:19.940 align:middle line:84%
have, regardless of what
psychedelic they took.

00:31:19.940 --> 00:31:23.930 align:middle line:84%
In fact, the same subject could
have dramatically different

00:31:23.930 --> 00:31:26.780 align:middle line:84%
experiences while taking
the same substance

00:31:26.780 --> 00:31:29.550 align:middle line:90%
on different occasions.

00:31:29.550 --> 00:31:32.360 align:middle line:84%
>> So this is not the
way pharmacology works.

00:31:32.360 --> 00:31:35.630 align:middle line:84%
You have a pretty good
idea what response

00:31:35.630 --> 00:31:39.050 align:middle line:84%
you would get with antibiotics
or whatever substance

00:31:39.050 --> 00:31:40.070 align:middle line:90%
we are talking about.

00:31:40.070 --> 00:31:43.070 align:middle line:84%
We are dealing with a catalyst,
and that the content is

00:31:43.070 --> 00:31:45.650 align:middle line:84%
not produced by the
substances, but that it's

00:31:45.650 --> 00:31:48.410 align:middle line:84%
released from the deep
unconscious realms

00:31:48.410 --> 00:31:51.710 align:middle line:84%
that current psychiatry and
psychology does not know about.

00:31:51.710 --> 00:31:54.470 align:middle line:84%
Because when it comes, they
think it's pathological.

00:31:54.470 --> 00:31:56.360 align:middle line:84%
They don't see it
as something that's

00:31:56.360 --> 00:31:59.750 align:middle line:90%
germane to the human psyche.

00:31:59.750 --> 00:32:03.050 align:middle line:84%
And then I started seeing it
as a telescope or a microscope.

00:32:03.050 --> 00:32:06.680 align:middle line:84%
With a telescope, we can
see galaxies that we cannot

00:32:06.680 --> 00:32:07.850 align:middle line:90%
normally study.

00:32:07.850 --> 00:32:11.210 align:middle line:10%
With a microscope, you
discover an enormous microworld

00:32:11.210 --> 00:32:13.910 align:middle line:10%
that is here, but we
are not aware of it

00:32:13.910 --> 00:32:17.390 align:middle line:10%
unless we have the proper tool.

00:32:17.390 --> 00:32:20.960 align:middle line:84%
So then I took it from the
laboratory to clinical practice

00:32:20.960 --> 00:32:22.940 align:middle line:84%
and started seeing
it as something

00:32:22.940 --> 00:32:27.060 align:middle line:84%
that's going to deepen and
intensify psychotherapy.

00:32:27.060 --> 00:32:30.450 align:middle line:84%
>> During this period, Stan won
a competition with a paper he

00:32:30.450 --> 00:32:32.520 align:middle line:90%
wrote about his realizations.

00:32:32.520 --> 00:32:34.770 align:middle line:84%
The prize earned
him the directorship

00:32:34.770 --> 00:32:39.150 align:middle line:84%
of the psychedelic program at
a newly built research center.

00:32:39.150 --> 00:32:41.070 align:middle line:84%
Just as in the
laboratory testing,

00:32:41.070 --> 00:32:44.010 align:middle line:84%
subjects in the clinical
tests had a broad range

00:32:44.010 --> 00:32:48.180 align:middle line:84%
of experiences, including
blissful and ecstatic ones.

00:32:48.180 --> 00:32:50.850 align:middle line:84%
And even emotionally
challenging experiences

00:32:50.850 --> 00:32:53.940 align:middle line:84%
were soothed as the session
ended and memories that

00:32:53.940 --> 00:32:55.980 align:middle line:90%
had surfaced were resolved.

00:32:55.980 --> 00:32:58.710 align:middle line:84%
Stan even noted that
the clinical sessions

00:32:58.710 --> 00:33:01.590 align:middle line:84%
seemed very similar to
classic psychotherapy.

00:33:01.590 --> 00:33:04.960 align:middle line:90%
But over time, patterns emerged.

00:33:04.960 --> 00:33:08.310 align:middle line:84%
>> The contents of the
unconscious were not stored

00:33:08.310 --> 00:33:11.160 align:middle line:84%
in the form of kind of
disconnected mosaic,

00:33:11.160 --> 00:33:14.670 align:middle line:84%
but they were forming certain
dynamic constellations.

00:33:14.670 --> 00:33:18.630 align:middle line:10%
Certain issues were
appearing on different levels

00:33:18.630 --> 00:33:21.450 align:middle line:10%
at different times
of their biography,

00:33:21.450 --> 00:33:25.690 align:middle line:10%
and they were creating
these dynamic packets that

00:33:25.690 --> 00:33:28.140 align:middle line:10%
were connected with the
same type of emotions

00:33:28.140 --> 00:33:30.030 align:middle line:10%
or physical feeling.

00:33:30.030 --> 00:33:32.940 align:middle line:84%
Let's say they would have
a choking constellation.

00:33:32.940 --> 00:33:35.700 align:middle line:84%
They would be near drowning
when they were seven

00:33:35.700 --> 00:33:38.820 align:middle line:84%
and being choked by an older
brother repeatedly when they

00:33:38.820 --> 00:33:41.250 align:middle line:90%
were four, then whooping cough.

00:33:41.250 --> 00:33:45.400 align:middle line:84%
But then the deeper level
was the choking at birth.

00:33:45.400 --> 00:33:51.490 align:middle line:84%
So I started talking about these
constellations, COEX systems.

00:33:51.490 --> 00:33:54.580 align:middle line:84%
>> In addition to the
understanding of COEX systems,

00:33:54.580 --> 00:33:57.760 align:middle line:84%
Stan observed how the
experiences of his clients

00:33:57.760 --> 00:34:01.270 align:middle line:84%
evolved dramatically during
a series of sessions.

00:34:01.270 --> 00:34:04.420 align:middle line:84%
>> Only the early sessions
seemed to have the nature

00:34:04.420 --> 00:34:07.780 align:middle line:84%
of the experiences that I
knew from psychoanalysis.

00:34:07.780 --> 00:34:09.730 align:middle line:84%
But then sooner or
later, even if we

00:34:09.730 --> 00:34:12.010 align:middle line:84%
are using sort of
just medium dosages,

00:34:12.010 --> 00:34:15.010 align:middle line:84%
people started talking about
being in a place where they

00:34:15.010 --> 00:34:17.870 align:middle line:84%
felt their life was threatened,
that they're going crazy,

00:34:17.870 --> 00:34:20.139 align:middle line:84%
they will never get
out of that state.

00:34:20.139 --> 00:34:23.710 align:middle line:84%
They started having experiences
of choking or nausea.

00:34:23.710 --> 00:34:26.350 align:middle line:84%
And then one after
another told me

00:34:26.350 --> 00:34:29.050 align:middle line:84%
that they believed that
what they are experiencing

00:34:29.050 --> 00:34:31.300 align:middle line:90%
must be a reliving of birth.

00:34:31.300 --> 00:34:34.480 align:middle line:84%
At a certain point, I
decided to test this.

00:34:34.480 --> 00:34:41.050 align:middle line:84%
And I took 300 micrograms
on my own at home.

00:34:41.050 --> 00:34:44.980 align:middle line:84%
Within an hour, I was in a
very, very difficult place.

00:34:44.980 --> 00:34:47.260 align:middle line:84%
On the wall, I had a painting,
some type of painting.

00:34:47.260 --> 00:34:51.310 align:middle line:84%
And there was one which was like
a stylized dog with a soldier.

00:34:51.310 --> 00:34:53.530 align:middle line:84%
They started
fighting, and then I

00:34:53.530 --> 00:34:56.590 align:middle line:84%
had the feeling that everything
was kind of closing in.

00:34:56.590 --> 00:34:59.230 align:middle line:84%
And very quickly,
I was in something

00:34:59.230 --> 00:35:03.070 align:middle line:84%
that I now call the
second perinatal matrix.

00:35:03.070 --> 00:35:07.450 align:middle line:84%
It was like a space where it
seemed absolutely hopeless.

00:35:07.450 --> 00:35:11.200 align:middle line:84%
Very, very uncomfortable
emotionally.

00:35:11.200 --> 00:35:14.530 align:middle line:84%
And then I started feeling
a pressure on my head.

00:35:14.530 --> 00:35:18.280 align:middle line:84%
I realized that I was somehow
stuck in the birth canal,

00:35:18.280 --> 00:35:21.670 align:middle line:84%
and all my life appeared to
be absolutely meaningless.

00:35:21.670 --> 00:35:25.420 align:middle line:84%
I started seeing the deep truth
in existential philosophy.

00:35:25.420 --> 00:35:27.320 align:middle line:90%
You know, life is absurd.

00:35:27.320 --> 00:35:29.140 align:middle line:90%
We go from nowhere to nowhere.

00:35:29.140 --> 00:35:32.020 align:middle line:84%
We start life as
infants in pain,

00:35:32.020 --> 00:35:34.300 align:middle line:84%
and this is how we
are going to end.

00:35:34.300 --> 00:35:37.480 align:middle line:84%
But even if I knew that
this was birth, then

00:35:37.480 --> 00:35:40.840 align:middle line:84%
somehow the thought came
that this state would not end

00:35:40.840 --> 00:35:44.050 align:middle line:90%
unless I find meaning in life.

00:35:44.050 --> 00:35:45.940 align:middle line:84%
And then I said,
well, it's knowledge.

00:35:45.940 --> 00:35:48.400 align:middle line:84%
And I saw myself
going to libraries,

00:35:48.400 --> 00:35:50.600 align:middle line:84%
devouring one book
after another.

00:35:50.600 --> 00:35:52.870 align:middle line:84%
And then it took me
to the end of my life

00:35:52.870 --> 00:35:55.190 align:middle line:84%
where I couldn't remember
what I had for dinner,

00:35:55.190 --> 00:35:58.300 align:middle line:84%
