00:39:35.025 --> 00:39:35.825 align:middle line:90%
Oscar?

00:39:35.825 --> 00:39:41.185 align:middle line:90%


00:39:41.185 --> 00:39:41.985 align:middle line:90%
Oscar?

00:39:41.985 --> 00:39:44.470 align:middle line:90%


00:39:44.470 --> 00:39:45.270 align:middle line:90%
Oh.

00:39:45.270 --> 00:39:52.870 align:middle line:90%


00:39:52.870 --> 00:39:56.200 align:middle line:84%
It was clear to me now
that my children's behavior

00:39:56.200 --> 00:39:58.120 align:middle line:84%
had been influenced
either by what

00:39:58.120 --> 00:40:00.220 align:middle line:84%
had happened while
they were in the womb

00:40:00.220 --> 00:40:04.485 align:middle line:90%
or during their actual birth.

00:40:04.485 --> 00:40:09.140 align:middle line:90%
>> Mama, I'm going to hide.

00:40:09.140 --> 00:40:11.960 align:middle line:90%
Come inside and hide.

00:40:11.960 --> 00:40:13.490 align:middle line:90%
I'm going to hide.

00:40:13.490 --> 00:40:16.490 align:middle line:84%
>> How could scientists so
easily dismiss the reality

00:40:16.490 --> 00:40:18.756 align:middle line:90%
of perinatal memories?

00:40:18.756 --> 00:40:21.600 align:middle line:90%
>> Come inside and hide.

00:40:21.600 --> 00:40:24.860 align:middle line:84%
>> The usual view about the
mind is that the mind's confined

00:40:24.860 --> 00:40:25.940 align:middle line:90%
to the head.

00:40:25.940 --> 00:40:30.410 align:middle line:84%
It's nothing but the
activity of the brain.

00:40:30.410 --> 00:40:34.250 align:middle line:10%
For the materialists who
represent the majority position

00:40:34.250 --> 00:40:37.610 align:middle line:10%
within academic
life and in science,

00:40:37.610 --> 00:40:41.330 align:middle line:10%
minds are what brains do, and
memories are stored materially

00:40:41.330 --> 00:40:42.170 align:middle line:10%
inside the brain.

00:40:42.170 --> 00:40:44.400 align:middle line:90%
It's all inside the brain.

00:40:44.400 --> 00:40:48.140 align:middle line:84%
I think that's an incredibly
truncated and narrow view.

00:40:48.140 --> 00:40:51.020 align:middle line:84%
First of all, I think
we access our memories

00:40:51.020 --> 00:40:52.100 align:middle line:90%
by morphic resonance.

00:40:52.100 --> 00:40:53.870 align:middle line:90%
They're not inside the brain.

00:40:53.870 --> 00:40:57.470 align:middle line:84%
And secondly, I think that
our consciousness, our minds

00:40:57.470 --> 00:40:59.720 align:middle line:84%
are not confined to the
inside of our heads,

00:40:59.720 --> 00:41:02.330 align:middle line:84%
but stretch out beyond
and through fields.

00:41:02.330 --> 00:41:04.700 align:middle line:84%
We're all used to the
idea of magnetic fields

00:41:04.700 --> 00:41:06.620 align:middle line:84%
being inside magnets
and stretching

00:41:06.620 --> 00:41:09.680 align:middle line:84%
beyond them or the
gravitational field of the Earth

00:41:09.680 --> 00:41:11.810 align:middle line:84%
being inside the Earth
and stretching out

00:41:11.810 --> 00:41:15.170 align:middle line:84%
into space invisibly, or
the fields of cell phones

00:41:15.170 --> 00:41:19.350 align:middle line:84%
being inside the cell phone and
stretching invisibly around it,

00:41:19.350 --> 00:41:20.450 align:middle line:90%
which is why they work.

00:41:20.450 --> 00:41:23.630 align:middle line:84%
And all matter now has
fields associated with it.

00:41:23.630 --> 00:41:24.890 align:middle line:90%
And of course, the brain does.

00:41:24.890 --> 00:41:27.050 align:middle line:84%
It has electromagnetic
fields you can measure

00:41:27.050 --> 00:41:28.820 align:middle line:90%
with an electroencephalograph.

00:41:28.820 --> 00:41:31.100 align:middle line:84%
But I think that the
fields of the mind

00:41:31.100 --> 00:41:34.460 align:middle line:84%
are much more extensive,
and these extended fields

00:41:34.460 --> 00:41:37.080 align:middle line:84%
of the mind are a
kind of morphic field.

00:41:37.080 --> 00:41:38.870 align:middle line:84%
So it's really a field
theory of the mind.

00:41:38.870 --> 00:41:42.180 align:middle line:90%


00:41:42.180 --> 00:41:44.910 align:middle line:84%
>> Now that I realized that
