pattern, you might say,

00:46:54.220 --> 00:47:00.450 align:middle line:84%
of the life process as it is
incarnated and reincarnated

00:47:00.450 --> 00:47:03.880 align:middle line:90%
in us as individuals.

00:47:03.880 --> 00:47:06.760 align:middle line:84%
>> When Stan discovered the work
of Lloyd deMause and the field

00:47:06.760 --> 00:47:10.690 align:middle line:84%
of psychohistory, he noted the
parallels between the imagery

00:47:10.690 --> 00:47:14.950 align:middle line:84%
used to goad people to war and
experiences that he and his

00:47:14.950 --> 00:47:17.650 align:middle line:84%
patients had during
their sessions.

00:47:17.650 --> 00:47:20.770 align:middle line:10%
It became clear to Stan that
these unconscious memories

00:47:20.770 --> 00:47:24.760 align:middle line:10%
of helplessness from the second
matrix and anger from the third

00:47:24.760 --> 00:47:28.380 align:middle line:10%
were driving factors
in the need for power.

00:47:28.380 --> 00:47:30.540 align:middle line:84%
This need for
control was clearly

00:47:30.540 --> 00:47:32.580 align:middle line:84%
evident in the book
"A Sexual Profile

00:47:32.580 --> 00:47:36.030 align:middle line:84%
of Men in Power," which detailed
a seven-year study of call

00:47:36.030 --> 00:47:39.840 align:middle line:84%
girls and madams whose primary
clients were politicians

00:47:39.840 --> 00:47:42.840 align:middle line:90%
and government officials.

00:47:42.840 --> 00:47:45.390 align:middle line:84%
The study found that
over 50% of those men

00:47:45.390 --> 00:47:48.870 align:middle line:84%
regularly hired prostitutes,
and more than half of them

00:47:48.870 --> 00:47:51.600 align:middle line:84%
demanded kinky or
sadomasochistic sex

00:47:51.600 --> 00:47:54.120 align:middle line:84%
as a means of coping
with the powerlessness

00:47:54.120 --> 00:47:57.560 align:middle line:84%
that they experienced
in government.

00:47:57.560 --> 00:47:59.850 align:middle line:84%
>> Nine months in a total
dependence on the maternal

00:47:59.850 --> 00:48:00.650 align:middle line:90%
organism.

00:48:00.650 --> 00:48:04.340 align:middle line:84%
Then there is this incredible
roller coaster of birth

00:48:04.340 --> 00:48:06.200 align:middle line:84%
that we are taken
through, and then

00:48:06.200 --> 00:48:09.140 align:middle line:84%
emerging in a total
dependence on the mother.

00:48:09.140 --> 00:48:12.020 align:middle line:84%
It leaves a very deep
fear of the feminine

00:48:12.020 --> 00:48:15.350 align:middle line:84%
in the male psyche, and
frequently a clumsy effort

00:48:15.350 --> 00:48:18.620 align:middle line:84%
to compensate for it, not
giving women the same rights,

00:48:18.620 --> 00:48:22.040 align:middle line:84%
not to treat them as
equal citizens, and so on.

00:48:22.040 --> 00:48:24.200 align:middle line:10%
Women go through that
also, but because

00:48:24.200 --> 00:48:27.140 align:middle line:10%
of their physiological function,
because of their anatomy,

00:48:27.140 --> 00:48:30.320 align:middle line:10%
they are able to
participate directly

00:48:30.320 --> 00:48:32.420 align:middle line:10%
in the process of creation.

00:48:32.420 --> 00:48:35.780 align:middle line:84%
The male participation
is very marginal.

00:48:35.780 --> 00:48:40.700 align:middle line:84%
It can take a few minutes,
and then it's over.

00:48:40.700 --> 00:48:43.970 align:middle line:84%
The way to resolve
traumatic unconscious memory

00:48:43.970 --> 00:48:49.410 align:middle line:84%
would be if that material fully
emerges into consciousness,

00:48:49.410 --> 00:48:50.960 align:middle line:90%
which will be therapeutic.

00:48:50.960 --> 00:48:52.610 align:middle line:84%
What can happen
in everyday life,

00:48:52.610 --> 00:48:56.180 align:middle line:84%
it comes close to the surface,
but that person does not

00:48:56.180 --> 00:48:58.220 align:middle line:90%
realize what it is exactly.

00:48:58.220 --> 00:49:02.120 align:middle line:84%
But they feel the need to
create a situation that

00:49:02.120 --> 00:49:04.080 align:middle line:90%
would involve those elements.

00:49:04.080 --> 00:49:06.470 align:middle line:84%
So for example, that
transition from the third

00:49:06.470 --> 00:49:11.160 align:middle line:84%
to the fourth matrix frequently
is experienced as fire.

00:49:11.160 --> 00:49:14.100 align:middle line:84%
I worked with some people
who were arsonists,

00:49:14.100 --> 00:49:17.040 align:middle line:90%
and they had this impulse.

00:49:17.040 --> 00:49:18.750 align:middle line:84%
They felt that
something fantastic

00:49:18.750 --> 00:49:22.500 align:middle line:84%
would happen if they could
experience a big fire.

00:49:22.500 --> 00:49:24.150 align:middle line:84%
When that happens,
they watched it

00:49:24.150 --> 00:49:28.080 align:middle line:84%
and feel excitement for a
while, but it is a real letdown.

00:49:28.080 --> 00:49:31.050 align:middle line:84%
They expected something
much more phenomenal.

00:49:31.050 --> 00:49:32.970 align:middle line:84%
But the drive can
be strong enough

00:49:32.970 --> 00:49:36.690 align:middle line:84%
to drive them to do
it again and again.

00:49:36.690 --> 00:49:39.540 align:middle line:84%
In a very similar
way, the third matrix

00:49:39.540 --> 00:49:41.910 align:middle line:84%
involves a lot of
sadomasochistic kind

00:49:41.910 --> 00:49:45.060 align:middle line:84%
of experiences where
you feel sexual arousal

00:49:45.060 --> 00:49:48.950 align:middle line:84%
and you feel confined and you
feel sort of choked, and so on.

00:49:48.950 --> 00:49:52.080 align:middle line:84%
It's a kind of unrecognized
healing impulse.

00:49:52.080 --> 00:49:53.880 align:middle line:84%
But for it to be
therapeutic, it would

00:49:53.880 --> 00:49:56.310 align:middle line:84%
have to involve
introspection, understanding

00:49:56.310 --> 00:49:58.170 align:middle line:84%
what you are dealing
with, and really

00:49:58.170 --> 00:50:02.800 align:middle line:84%
be fully consciously in
touch with the material.

00:50:02.800 --> 00:50:06.460 align:middle line:84%
>> Nothing the conscious mind
can think of will ever satisfy

00:50:06.460 --> 00:50:07.660 align:middle line:90%
the unconscious.

00:50:07.660 --> 00:50:10.450 align:middle line:84%
It has to originate from the
unconscious to be cleared.

00:50:10.450 --> 00:50:14.380 align:middle line:90%


00:50:14.380 --> 00:50:17.170 align:middle line:84%
After hearing so many
of Stan's stories,

00:50:17.170 --> 00:50:19.300 align:middle line:84%
it was time for me to
find out what shadows

00:50:19.300 --> 00:50:21.670 align:middle line:90%
were lurking in my unconscious.

00:50:21.670 --> 00:50:24.100 align:middle line:84%
Would they be as dark
as what Stan had seen?

00:50:24.100 --> 00:50:28.840 align:middle line:84%
And if so, would I have the
courage to confront them?

00:50:28.840 --> 00:50:32.420 align:middle line:84%
Rule number one,
never do this alone.

00:50:32.420 --> 00:50:35.590 align:middle line:84%
The sitter is there to
keep you safe, ground you,

00:50:35.590 --> 00:50:38.440 align:middle line:84%
and more importantly,
to hold the space

00:50:38.440 --> 00:50:41.560 align:middle line:84%
so that you can completely
open to whatever comes.

00:50:41.560 --> 00:50:45.030 align:middle line:90%


00:50:45.030 --> 00:50:47.070 align:middle line:84%
As the LSD took
effect, there was

00:50:47.070 --> 00:50:50.070 align:middle line:90%
a flood of geometric imagery.

00:50:50.070 --> 00:50:52.290 align:middle line:84%
Some people call
retinal discharge,

00:50:52.290 --> 00:50:55.140 align:middle line:84%
but now I think I was
seeing fractals or even

00:50:55.140 --> 00:50:57.090 align:middle line:84%
the dimension that
holds the blueprints

00:50:57.090 --> 00:50:58.110 align:middle line:90%
of the physical world.

00:50:58.110 --> 00:51:02.730 align:middle line:90%


00:51:02.730 --> 00:51:04.980 align:middle line:84%
Soon it transitioned
into Christina.

00:51:04.980 --> 00:51:08.760 align:middle line:84%
And then, as though I was
seeing through Christina's eyes,

00:51:08.760 --> 00:51:10.500 align:middle line:90%
it was Stan.

00:51:10.500 --> 00:51:12.990 align:middle line:84%
There was a sadness
as she realized

00:51:12.990 --> 00:51:15.000 align:middle line:90%
that she was leaving him.

00:51:15.000 --> 00:51:18.750 align:middle line:84%
But then Stan transitioned
into my father and Christina

00:51:18.750 --> 00:51:19.770 align:middle line:90%
dissolved into me.

00:51:19.770 --> 00:51:34.520 align:middle line:90%


00:51:34.520 --> 00:51:38.350 align:middle line:84%
The pain was so intense that I
knew it couldn't just be mine.

00:51:38.350 --> 00:51:41.210 align:middle line:90%


00:51:41.210 --> 00:51:43.190 align:middle line:84%
I actually felt as
though I was choking.

00:51:43.190 --> 00:51:46.830 align:middle line:90%


00:51:46.830 --> 00:51:49.860 align:middle line:84%
In that moment, I
understood that although I

00:51:49.860 --> 00:51:53.160 align:middle line:84%
might have been triggered by
the pending death of my father,

00:51:53.160 --> 00:51:56.610 align:middle line:84%
I was also tapping into
the collective sadness.

00:51:56.610 --> 00:51:58.800 align:middle line:84%
And what a depth
of it there was.

00:51:58.800 --> 00:52:03.810 align:middle line:84%
Addiction, drugs, alcohol,
sex, compulsive behavior,

00:52:03.810 --> 00:52:07.770 align:middle line:84%
anything to dissolve back into
the formless ocean of love

00:52:07.770 --> 00:52:10.860 align:middle line:84%
and avoid this unbearable
sadness of separation.

00:52:10.860 --> 00:52:16.580 align:middle line:90%


00:52:16.580 --> 00:52:19.580 align:middle line:84%
It took me two days
to feel whole again.

00:52:19.580 --> 00:52:21.500 align:middle line:84%
If it hadn't been
for my kids to think

00:52:21.500 --> 00:52:24.130 align:middle line:84%
about or the sitter
to talk to, I

00:52:24.130 --> 00:52:25.880 align:middle line:84%
don't know if I would
have come out of it.

00:52:25.880 --> 00:52:28.610 align:middle line:90%


00:52:28.610 --> 00:52:32.510 align:middle line:84%
But because I had grieved my
dad's death before he died,

00:52:32.510 --> 00:52:34.880 align:middle line:84%
I was able to listen
to his daydreams

00:52:34.880 --> 00:52:37.590 align:middle line:84%
during those last
weeks of his life.

00:52:37.590 --> 00:52:40.220 align:middle line:84%
And when he finally
slipped into a coma,

00:52:40.220 --> 00:52:43.400 align:middle line:84%
I knew how to help him
detach from his body so he

00:52:43.400 --> 00:52:46.100 align:middle line:90%
wasn't afraid or in pain.

00:52:46.100 --> 00:52:49.460 align:middle line:84%
He lay like that for 28
hours, and then an hour

00:52:49.460 --> 00:52:52.700 align:middle line:84%
before my daughter's last
ballet performance, he died.

00:52:52.700 --> 00:52:55.670 align:middle line:90%


00:52:55.670 --> 00:52:59.030 align:middle line:84%
I was filming while Charlotte
danced when suddenly I

00:52:59.030 --> 00:53:01.760 align:middle line:84%
remembered that he had
sat in that theater,

00:53:01.760 --> 00:53:04.970 align:middle line:84%
and I remembered exactly
where he had sat.

00:53:04.970 --> 00:53:08.660 align:middle line:84%
The memory was so clear
that I realized that I

00:53:08.660 --> 00:53:10.490 align:middle line:90%
was seeing through his eyes.

00:53:10.490 --> 00:53:12.920 align:middle line:84%
His spirit was
there in the theater

00:53:12.920 --> 00:53:14.750 align:middle line:84%
to watch his
granddaughter dance.

00:53:14.750 --> 00:53:26.850 align:middle line:90%


00:53:26.850 --> 00:53:30.120 align:middle line:84%
After the performance,
I went to help my mom.

00:53:30.120 --> 00:53:31.890 align:middle line:84%
When I had finally
cleaned the space

00:53:31.890 --> 00:53:35.370 align:middle line:84%
so that she could remember him
in better health, I went home.

00:53:35.370 --> 00:53:37.950 align:middle line:90%


00:53:37.950 --> 00:53:41.070 align:middle line:84%
A few hours later, I
let the tears well up

00:53:41.070 --> 00:53:44.820 align:middle line:84%
and felt myself once again
pulled out by my heart.

00:53:44.820 --> 00:53:47.760 align:middle line:84%
But because I knew that
I could survive it,

00:53:47.760 --> 00:53:53.270 align:middle line:84%
I allowed the sadness to
flow, and it felt amazing.

00:53:53.270 --> 00:53:55.310 align:middle line:84%
If I hadn't witnessed
Stan's courage

00:53:55.310 --> 00:53:58.310 align:middle line:84%
and trusted his example,
I doubt any of that

00:53:58.310 --> 00:54:01.490 align:middle line:90%
would have happened.

00:54:01.490 --> 00:54:03.430 align:middle line:84%
He wasn't afraid to
confront the darkness.

00:54:03.430 --> 00:54:11.000 align:middle line:90%


00:54:11.000 --> 00:54:15.350 align:middle line:84%
In 1967, Stan was invited to
continue his research at Johns

00:54:15.350 --> 00:54:17.450 align:middle line:90%
Hopkins University in Maryland.

00:54:17.450 --> 00:54:19.250 align:middle line:84%
But pushback
against psychedelics

00:54:19.250 --> 00:54:22.580 align:middle line:84%
was growing, inflamed by
flawed studies engineered

00:54:22.580 --> 00:54:23.690 align:middle line:90%
to generate fear.

00:54:23.690 --> 00:54:26.270 align:middle line:90%


00:54:26.270 --> 00:54:29.480 align:middle line:84%
>> We have children that are
born without legs or arms,

00:54:29.480 --> 00:54:33.050 align:middle line:84%
the kind of thing we've seen
after thalidomide exposure.

00:54:33.050 --> 00:54:35.780 align:middle line:84%
>> Even though the studies
were eventually dismissed,

00:54:35.780 --> 00:54:39.390 align:middle line:84%
the culture was reeling from
the impact of psychedelics.

00:54:39.390 --> 00:54:42.350 align:middle line:84%
As a result, the research
program at Johns Hopkins

00:54:42.350 --> 00:54:44.090 align:middle line:90%
University was terminated.

00:54:44.090 --> 00:54:46.250 align:middle line:10%
Fortunately for
Stan, the program

00:54:46.250 --> 00:54:49.730 align:middle line:10%
at Spring Grove Psychiatric
Hospital was still operational.

00:54:49.730 --> 00:54:52.220 align:middle line:84%
While there, he
continued his research,

00:54:52.220 --> 00:54:55.680 align:middle line:84%
encountering even more
intriguing patients.

00:54:55.680 --> 00:54:58.340 align:middle line:84%
>> This was a patient who had
some of the most difficult

00:54:58.340 --> 00:55:00.470 align:middle line:84%
pathology, if you want
to call it that way,

00:55:00.470 --> 00:55:01.820 align:middle line:90%
that I have ever seen.

00:55:01.820 --> 00:55:04.620 align:middle line:90%
She was four years in prison.

00:55:04.620 --> 00:55:08.240 align:middle line:84%
And while on parole, she
became a multiple drug addict.

00:55:08.240 --> 00:55:11.820 align:middle line:84%
She had very difficult
episodes of depression.

00:55:11.820 --> 00:55:13.650 align:middle line:84%
So it was kind of
a life decision,

00:55:13.650 --> 00:55:16.070 align:middle line:84%
and so we decided
to take our chances.

00:55:16.070 --> 00:55:19.040 align:middle line:84%
So she had two very
powerful sessions.

00:55:19.040 --> 00:55:21.770 align:middle line:84%
She was from a family
where there was alcoholism,

00:55:21.770 --> 00:55:24.800 align:middle line:84%
there was abuse,
there was incest.

00:55:24.800 --> 00:55:28.370 align:middle line:84%
And then in the third session,
suddenly she started crying,

00:55:28.370 --> 00:55:30.030 align:middle line:90%
she started screaming.

00:55:30.030 --> 00:55:34.650 align:middle line:84%
And then a vicious
expression in her eyes.

00:55:34.650 --> 00:55:35.454 align:middle line:90%
Incredible.

00:55:35.454 --> 00:55:38.420 align:middle line:84%
Incredibly sort of
evil expression.

00:55:38.420 --> 00:55:43.180 align:middle line:84%
And this very deep voice
came and introduced itself,

00:55:43.180 --> 00:55:44.870 align:middle line:90%
himself as the devil.

00:55:44.870 --> 00:55:49.670 align:middle line:84%
And then came this barrage
of insults and threats.

00:55:49.670 --> 00:55:53.450 align:middle line:84%
There was information
that the patient as such

00:55:53.450 --> 00:55:55.790 align:middle line:90%
could not have known.

00:55:55.790 --> 00:55:59.270 align:middle line:84%
I had a wonderful nurse
that was a southern Baptist,

00:55:59.270 --> 00:56:00.472 align:middle line:90%
and she was shaking.

00:56:00.472 --> 00:56:02.180 align:middle line:84%
I thought she was
getting a heart attack.

00:56:02.180 --> 00:56:06.830 align:middle line:84%
So I was watching the patient,
and the nurse at one point--

00:56:06.830 --> 00:56:10.040 align:middle line:84%
I said, well, this is obviously
the Jungian archetype that's

00:56:10.040 --> 00:56:11.450 align:middle line:90%
manifesting here.

00:56:11.450 --> 00:56:13.400 align:middle line:84%
But maybe for that
kind of archetype,

00:56:13.400 --> 00:56:16.800 align:middle line:84%
the crucifix would
be the best remedy.

00:56:16.800 --> 00:56:21.750 align:middle line:84%
As I was reacting emotionally,
it was just becoming more real.

00:56:21.750 --> 00:56:23.930 align:middle line:84%
So I started
meditating on light.

00:56:23.930 --> 00:56:26.570 align:middle line:84%
I knew that from my
spiritual reading

00:56:26.570 --> 00:56:30.590 align:middle line:84%
that these creatures
don't like light.

00:56:30.590 --> 00:56:35.240 align:middle line:84%
Suddenly, it stopped
the way it started.

00:56:35.240 --> 00:56:37.250 align:middle line:90%
Everything relaxed.

00:56:37.250 --> 00:56:39.470 align:middle line:84%
Then as she was coming
down, we sort of

00:56:39.470 --> 00:56:41.640 align:middle line:90%
started talking about it.

00:56:41.640 --> 00:56:44.390 align:middle line:84%
And I realized she
remembered only what

00:56:44.390 --> 00:56:45.980 align:middle line:90%
happened before this episode.

00:56:45.980 --> 00:56:49.760 align:middle line:84%
And what happened after, there's
just total amnesia for this.

00:56:49.760 --> 00:56:52.100 align:middle line:84%
And I wondered if I
should sort of bring that

00:56:52.100 --> 00:56:56.630 align:middle line:84%
up and talk about it, and I
decided not to do it at all.

00:56:56.630 --> 00:56:58.770 align:middle line:90%
But she herself felt wonderful.

00:56:58.770 --> 00:57:00.440 align:middle line:84%
And then very
shortly afterwards,

00:57:00.440 --> 00:57:03.590 align:middle line:84%
she left the hospital
and probably was a little

00:57:03.590 --> 00:57:05.900 align:middle line:90%
lying on the questionnaire.

00:57:05.900 --> 00:57:10.670 align:middle line:90%
She got a job as a taxi driver.

00:57:10.670 --> 00:57:13.550 align:middle line:84%
>> But despite the tremendous
success of his work,

00:57:13.550 --> 00:57:16.460 align:middle line:90%
the program lost funding.

00:57:16.460 --> 00:57:18.890 align:middle line:10%
>> We were finding it more
and more difficult to continue

00:57:18.890 --> 00:57:19.690 align:middle line:10%
the research.

00:57:19.690 --> 00:57:23.210 align:middle line:84%
And I had a lot of material,
so I really wanted a sabbatical

00:57:23.210 --> 00:57:25.460 align:middle line:90%
and do some writing.

00:57:25.460 --> 00:57:29.090 align:middle line:84%
And I got an invitation
from several publishers

00:57:29.090 --> 00:57:30.410 align:middle line:90%
so I could take a year off.

00:57:30.410 --> 00:57:33.290 align:middle line:84%
And I went to a party
in New York City,

00:57:33.290 --> 00:57:35.990 align:middle line:84%
and there was
Michael Murphy there,

00:57:35.990 --> 00:57:37.400 align:middle line:90%
the co-founder of Esalen.

00:57:37.400 --> 00:57:41.930 align:middle line:84%
>> When I met Stan first in
'65, he was probably the best

00:57:41.930 --> 00:57:44.840 align:middle line:84%
looking man in the human
potential movement.

00:57:44.840 --> 00:57:47.780 align:middle line:84%
I mean, he was as good
looking as Richard Burton.

00:57:47.780 --> 00:57:50.000 align:middle line:84%
>> He said, so Stan, what
are you doing these days?

00:57:50.000 --> 00:57:52.310 align:middle line:84%
I said, well, I'm
actually taking a year off

00:57:52.310 --> 00:57:53.280 align:middle line:90%
to write a book.

00:57:53.280 --> 00:57:56.320 align:middle line:84%
And he said, why don't
you come to Esalen?

00:57:56.320 --> 00:58:00.160 align:middle line:84%
>> It was my instinct as a
director and producer of this

00:58:00.160 --> 00:58:02.160 align:middle line:90%
ongoing theater at Esalen.

00:58:02.160 --> 00:58:04.160 align:middle line:90%
He was perfect.

00:58:04.160 --> 00:58:07.570 align:middle line:10%
And of course, we had
been right in the middle

00:58:07.570 --> 00:58:11.800 align:middle line:10%
of a lot of experimentation
with psychedelics.

00:58:11.800 --> 00:58:14.980 align:middle line:84%
And although psychedelics
were not my ally,

00:58:14.980 --> 00:58:20.980 align:middle line:84%
Stan represented not only
another doorway into this,

00:58:20.980 --> 00:58:23.680 align:middle line:90%
but also sobriety.

00:58:23.680 --> 00:58:25.930 align:middle line:84%
I mean, he actually
thought about it.

00:58:25.930 --> 00:58:28.840 align:middle line:10%
Tim pretended to think
about it, but he just

00:58:28.840 --> 00:58:33.430 align:middle line:10%
proclaimed a vision of
taking LSD every Sunday.

00:58:33.430 --> 00:58:35.500 align:middle line:84%
If it's good, just
have more of it.

00:58:35.500 --> 00:58:39.760 align:middle line:84%
And we saw disaster after
disaster during the '60s.

00:58:39.760 --> 00:58:42.160 align:middle line:84%
So Bob Schwartz
gave us some money,

00:58:42.160 --> 00:58:46.450 align:middle line:84%
and Esalen provided a beautiful
house, and off we went.

00:58:46.450 --> 00:58:52.120 align:middle line:10%
And he became the leading force
in our overall programming

00:58:52.120 --> 00:58:55.060 align:middle line:10%
for most of the
years he was there.

00:58:55.060 --> 00:58:57.220 align:middle line:84%
>> Besides our
breathwork workshops,

00:58:57.220 --> 00:59:00.130 align:middle line:84%
we offered then
months-long workshops.

00:59:00.130 --> 00:59:02.980 align:middle line:84%
People were coming to Esalen
from all over the world,

00:59:02.980 --> 00:59:05.620 align:middle line:84%
and they didn't want to
take just one workshop.

00:59:05.620 --> 00:59:07.960 align:middle line:10%
So this gave me a
chance to choose

00:59:07.960 --> 00:59:11.200 align:middle line:10%
a topic I was interested
in and see who in the world

00:59:11.200 --> 00:59:13.600 align:middle line:10%
was doing some
cutting-edge research

00:59:13.600 --> 00:59:16.030 align:middle line:10%
and invite those
people, and then

00:59:16.030 --> 00:59:20.680 align:middle line:10%
always finding 36 people who
would want to do it with us.

00:59:20.680 --> 00:59:24.680 align:middle line:84%
>> One popular program combined
vipassana with breath work.

00:59:24.680 --> 00:59:28.230 align:middle line:84%
>> I think of a time when
we were holding our large

00:59:28.230 --> 00:59:31.450 align:middle line:84%
holotropic breathwork and
Buddhist practice retreats.

00:59:31.450 --> 00:59:35.020 align:middle line:10%
And there's a room full of
some hundreds of people,

00:59:35.020 --> 00:59:38.230 align:middle line:10%
doing the breathwork
after we had meditated,

00:59:38.230 --> 00:59:40.680 align:middle line:10%
going through these profound
openings with this music

00:59:40.680 --> 00:59:41.480 align:middle line:10%
playing.

00:59:41.480 --> 00:59:43.725 align:middle line:84%
Some people are in
heavenly states,

00:59:43.725 --> 00:59:45.850 align:middle line:84%
and some people feel like
they're dying and getting

00:59:45.850 --> 00:59:48.670 align:middle line:84%
reborn, and some people
have past life experiences

00:59:48.670 --> 00:59:50.860 align:middle line:84%
or turning into
birds or animals,

00:59:50.860 --> 00:59:53.950 align:middle line:84%
and some people are having the
reliving of their childhood.

00:59:53.950 --> 00:59:55.420 align:middle line:90%
Every possible thing.

00:59:55.420 --> 00:59:57.490 align:middle line:84%
It's like being in
Dante's "Inferno"

00:59:57.490 --> 01:00:00.610 align:middle line:84%
and "Purgatorio" and "Paradiso"
all at the same time.

01:00:00.610 --> 01:00:03.610 align:middle line:84%
And it's really quite marvelous,
because it's so well held

01:00:03.610 --> 01:00:06.430 align:middle line:90%
and tended by the facilitators.

01:00:06.430 --> 01:00:10.000 align:middle line:84%
And then when things get really
dicey, they call Stan over.

01:00:10.000 --> 01:00:14.770 align:middle line:84%
So I remember one who was
a multiple personality who

01:00:14.770 --> 01:00:17.650 align:middle line:84%
had different alters that
would show themselves

01:00:17.650 --> 01:00:19.060 align:middle line:90%
at different points.

01:00:19.060 --> 01:00:22.000 align:middle line:84%
And one of them
was really demonic.

01:00:22.000 --> 01:00:25.030 align:middle line:84%
And this whole demonic
side started to come out.

01:00:25.030 --> 01:00:26.840 align:middle line:84%
Like, (SCRATCHY VOICE)
if you come near me,

01:00:26.840 --> 01:00:29.100 align:middle line:90%
I will slash and kill you.

01:00:29.100 --> 01:00:31.600 align:middle line:84%
So the facilitators were
a little bit nervous,

01:00:31.600 --> 01:00:35.350 align:middle line:84%
because the voice and the
aggression of this demon--

01:00:35.350 --> 01:00:38.890 align:middle line:84%
you try to fix or help
me and I will get you

01:00:38.890 --> 01:00:40.390 align:middle line:84%
and I will kill
you and slash you.

01:00:40.390 --> 01:00:43.420 align:middle line:84%
It was not an easy
person to be tending.

01:00:43.420 --> 01:00:45.190 align:middle line:84%
So they called Stan
over, because it

01:00:45.190 --> 01:00:48.310 align:middle line:84%
seemed like this demon
wanted to eat everybody.

01:00:48.310 --> 01:00:51.550 align:middle line:84%
And Stan came over
very calm and cool

01:00:51.550 --> 01:00:54.940 align:middle line:84%
and sat down and said,
tell me more, you know?

01:00:54.940 --> 01:00:56.200 align:middle line:90%
You're a demon.

01:00:56.200 --> 01:00:57.340 align:middle line:90%
You have some powers.

01:00:57.340 --> 01:00:59.020 align:middle line:10%
What are those powers you have?

01:00:59.020 --> 01:01:01.540 align:middle line:84%
And who do you think you
really are as a demon?

01:01:01.540 --> 01:01:04.097 align:middle line:84%
I mean, do you really know
what your identity is?

01:01:04.097 --> 01:01:05.680 align:middle line:84%
He didn't probably
ask it in that way.

01:01:05.680 --> 01:01:08.800 align:middle line:84%
But he began to look
directly at the demon,

01:01:08.800 --> 01:01:11.207 align:middle line:84%
say, you don't know really
where you come from,

01:01:11.207 --> 01:01:12.040 align:middle line:90%
do you, who you are?

01:01:12.040 --> 01:01:14.200 align:middle line:84%
I'm very pleased to meet
you, but you don't--

01:01:14.200 --> 01:01:17.630 align:middle line:84%
and the demon started to
get confused and start

01:01:17.630 --> 01:01:18.430 align:middle line:90%
to look around.

01:01:18.430 --> 01:01:21.640 align:middle line:84%
And it was like instead of
being afraid of the demon,

01:01:21.640 --> 01:01:26.530 align:middle line:84%
Stan met this demonic energy
with a kind of curiosity

01:01:26.530 --> 01:01:29.140 align:middle line:84%
and interest and fearlessness
that the demon had never

01:01:29.140 --> 01:01:29.950 align:middle line:90%
met before.

01:01:29.950 --> 01:01:32.260 align:middle line:84%
And it started to
kind of lose its way,

01:01:32.260 --> 01:01:35.140 align:middle line:84%
and then the whole
thing morphed.

01:01:35.140 --> 01:01:38.530 align:middle line:84%
Magic happened when other
people were frightened.

01:01:38.530 --> 01:01:40.960 align:middle line:84%
That kind of innocence
that Stan has,

01:01:40.960 --> 01:01:43.910 align:middle line:84%
it's like this giant kid
wandering around, saying, wow.

01:01:43.910 --> 01:01:44.710 align:middle line:90%
Look at that.

01:01:44.710 --> 01:01:51.025 align:middle line:84%
He has this tremendous
appreciation for everything.

01:01:51.025 --> 01:01:57.340 align:middle line:10%
>> In 1974, Stan was about 43
years old, and I was about 24,

01:01:57.340 --> 01:02:00.490 align:middle line:10%
working at Esalen as a
night guard and then writing

01:02:00.490 --> 01:02:03.430 align:middle line:10%
my dissertation during the day.

01:02:03.430 --> 01:02:08.470 align:middle line:84%
And we got a call at about
4:30, 4:30 in the morning.

01:02:08.470 --> 01:02:12.670 align:middle line:84%
The night guard who was on that
night said, we've got a crisis,

01:02:12.670 --> 01:02:17.250 align:middle line:84%
and we need you guys
here right away.

01:02:17.250 --> 01:02:19.920 align:middle line:84%
1:00 AM to 5:30 every
morning we would

01:02:19.920 --> 01:02:24.180 align:middle line:84%
let in people from outside
of Esalen to use the baths.

01:02:24.180 --> 01:02:27.540 align:middle line:84%
A young man had taken
LSD with his girlfriend

01:02:27.540 --> 01:02:30.630 align:middle line:84%
and started to flip out at
some point during the session.

01:02:30.630 --> 01:02:32.400 align:middle line:90%
Became violently paranoid.

01:02:32.400 --> 01:02:35.880 align:middle line:84%
The girlfriend had
escaped from the guy.

01:02:35.880 --> 01:02:39.600 align:middle line:84%
He had gone up the
hill to their van.

01:02:39.600 --> 01:02:41.410 align:middle line:84%
All we knew was that
he's got a knife.

01:02:41.410 --> 01:02:42.210 align:middle line:90%
He's naked.

01:02:42.210 --> 01:02:45.870 align:middle line:84%
He's psychotically
paranoid and violent.

01:02:45.870 --> 01:02:49.360 align:middle line:84%
As we're approaching the
van, I'm thinking to myself,

01:02:49.360 --> 01:02:50.160 align:middle line:90%
oh, this is great.

01:02:50.160 --> 01:02:53.820 align:middle line:84%
Just because I'm writing
a dissertation on LSD

01:02:53.820 --> 01:03:00.680 align:middle line:84%
psychotherapy, I'm now in
a life and death situation.

01:03:00.680 --> 01:03:04.250 align:middle line:84%
So Stan opens the
sliding van door.

01:03:04.250 --> 01:03:06.600 align:middle line:84%
The bottle is thrown
right by his head.

01:03:06.600 --> 01:03:08.930 align:middle line:84%
And then he goes in,
picks up a blanket,

01:03:08.930 --> 01:03:12.060 align:middle line:84%
wraps it around the man,
and puts him in a bear hug

01:03:12.060 --> 01:03:12.990 align:middle line:90%
and says, OK.

01:03:12.990 --> 01:03:15.912 align:middle line:84%
You've taken a very
powerful psychoactive drug.

01:03:15.912 --> 01:03:17.870 align:middle line:84%
I want you to close your
eyes and pay attention

01:03:17.870 --> 01:03:19.360 align:middle line:90%
to what's going on inside you.

01:03:19.360 --> 01:03:23.610 align:middle line:90%


01:03:23.610 --> 01:03:26.610 align:middle line:84%
Within about 15
minutes, the young man

01:03:26.610 --> 01:03:30.240 align:middle line:84%
was laughing at himself, but
at the same time embarrassed

01:03:30.240 --> 01:03:32.940 align:middle line:90%
for what he had caused.

01:03:32.940 --> 01:03:36.360 align:middle line:84%
It was a real testament to
Stan's personal courage,

01:03:36.360 --> 01:03:41.100 align:middle line:84%
but it also was an illustration
of his whole philosophy

01:03:41.100 --> 01:03:42.840 align:middle line:90%
of trusting the psyche.

01:03:42.840 --> 01:03:46.130 align:middle line:90%


01:03:46.130 --> 01:03:48.260 align:middle line:84%
The very first
lecture that I ever

01:03:48.260 --> 01:03:51.980 align:middle line:84%
heard Stan give in
March of 1974 at Esalen,

01:03:51.980 --> 01:03:54.770 align:middle line:84%
I asked him at the
end, what do you

01:03:54.770 --> 01:03:59.630 align:middle line:84%
do in the case of someone who's
in a really bad trip where

01:03:59.630 --> 01:04:02.372 align:middle line:84%
they're descending
into an incessant loop

01:04:02.372 --> 01:04:03.830 align:middle line:84%
that they can't
get out of and they

01:04:03.830 --> 01:04:05.480 align:middle line:84%
feel like they're
losing their sanity?

01:04:05.480 --> 01:04:08.720 align:middle line:84%
And these things can have
enduring effects too.

01:04:08.720 --> 01:04:12.440 align:middle line:84%
And he said with a kind
of poetic conciseness

01:04:12.440 --> 01:04:14.690 align:middle line:84%
that I've never
forgotten, he just said,

01:04:14.690 --> 01:04:16.640 align:middle line:84%
the full experience
of an emotion

01:04:16.640 --> 01:04:20.400 align:middle line:84%
is the funeral pyre
of the emotion.

01:04:20.400 --> 01:04:25.430 align:middle line:84%
And he just pointed out that we
have a tendency to, of course,

01:04:25.430 --> 01:04:29.870 align:middle line:84%
wall ourselves off from
the pain, the scary things

01:04:29.870 --> 01:04:31.790 align:middle line:84%
in our psyche that
are trying to emerge.

01:04:31.790 --> 01:04:36.290 align:middle line:84%
But he says, that's actually
the way out of the pathology

01:04:36.290 --> 01:04:37.760 align:middle line:90%
of the suffering.

01:04:37.760 --> 01:04:42.220 align:middle line:84%
So he was able to convey
with that one sentence

01:04:42.220 --> 01:04:47.660 align:middle line:84%
the idea that bad trips and
negative material, which

01:04:47.660 --> 01:04:51.290 align:middle line:84%
Tim Leary did not
prepare the masses for,

01:04:51.290 --> 01:04:59.360 align:middle line:84%
were actually a royal road
to transformative healing.

01:04:59.360 --> 01:05:03.020 align:middle line:84%
>> I think it's essential when
we discuss psychedelics now

01:05:03.020 --> 01:05:06.350 align:middle line:84%
to talk about the
challenging experiences,

01:05:06.350 --> 01:05:08.510 align:middle line:90%
and that it's not all easy.

01:05:08.510 --> 01:05:12.500 align:middle line:84%
MAPS does psychedelic harm
reduction at Burning Man

01:05:12.500 --> 01:05:15.060 align:middle line:84%
and at festivals
all over the world.

01:05:15.060 --> 01:05:17.720 align:middle line:84%
And one of our main
principles is "difficult

01:05:17.720 --> 01:05:19.760 align:middle line:90%
is not the same as bad."

01:05:19.760 --> 01:05:22.220 align:middle line:84%
And I think that's where
with psychedelic therapy

01:05:22.220 --> 01:05:26.040 align:middle line:84%
right now we prepare people
in a much different way

01:05:26.040 --> 01:05:28.430 align:middle line:84%
and really talk about a lot
of the kernels of wisdom

01:05:28.430 --> 01:05:32.440 align:middle line:84%
will come wrapped in these
very difficult experiences.

01:05:32.440 --> 01:05:36.160 align:middle line:84%
>> Stan recognized early on that
existing schools of psychology

01:05:36.160 --> 01:05:39.310 align:middle line:84%
couldn't explain the profound
experiences and resulting

01:05:39.310 --> 01:05:43.120 align:middle line:84%
transformations that he
and his patients underwent.

01:05:43.120 --> 01:05:45.250 align:middle line:84%
Even before moving
to Esalen, Stan

01:05:45.250 --> 01:05:47.440 align:middle line:84%
worked with Abe
Maslow and Tony Sutich

01:05:47.440 --> 01:05:49.930 align:middle line:84%
to develop transpersonal
psychology, which

01:05:49.930 --> 01:05:52.720 align:middle line:84%
recognized the spiritual
nature of humanity

01:05:52.720 --> 01:05:56.350 align:middle line:84%
and the importance of memories
from our time in the womb

01:05:56.350 --> 01:05:58.270 align:middle line:90%
and beyond.

01:05:58.270 --> 01:06:01.150 align:middle line:84%
>> We got to the point where
we were very satisfied with

01:06:01.150 --> 01:06:04.840 align:middle line:84%
the kind of new psychology,
but we had no idea how we could

01:06:04.840 --> 01:06:10.030 align:middle line:84%
possibly link that gap between
this kind of system that we

01:06:10.030 --> 01:06:13.660 align:middle line:84%
created and what we knew as
the scientific psychology.

01:06:13.660 --> 01:06:17.090 align:middle line:84%
And that's where meeting Fritjof
Capra and reading his book,

01:06:17.090 --> 01:06:20.570 align:middle line:84%
"The Tao of Physics," was
extremely important for me.

01:06:20.570 --> 01:06:24.040 align:middle line:10%
Frances Vaughan
invited him to Tiburon

01:06:24.040 --> 01:06:26.530 align:middle line:10%
to meet transpersonal
psychologists,

01:06:26.530 --> 01:06:28.370 align:middle line:10%
and we really hit it off.

01:06:28.370 --> 01:06:30.980 align:middle line:10%
>> We planned these
seminars together,

01:06:30.980 --> 01:06:34.840 align:middle line:10%
which we called journeys
beyond space and time.

01:06:34.840 --> 01:06:41.170 align:middle line:10%
And those were an inner journey
of transpersonal experiences

01:06:41.170 --> 01:06:44.890 align:middle line:10%
and the outer journey
of physicists delving

01:06:44.890 --> 01:06:48.010 align:middle line:10%
into matter at the atomic
and subatomic level.

01:06:48.010 --> 01:06:52.030 align:middle line:84%
>> Fritjof would take the
morning and tell people how

01:06:52.030 --> 01:06:57.010 align:middle line:84%
scientists, physicists now
see the world of matter.

01:06:57.010 --> 01:07:03.220 align:middle line:84%
>> I presented perception of
reality where the solid objects

01:07:03.220 --> 01:07:08.590 align:middle line:84%
of our everyday experience
dissolve into energy patterns

01:07:08.590 --> 01:07:14.020 align:middle line:84%
and where particles can travel
backward and forward in time,

01:07:14.020 --> 01:07:17.950 align:middle line:84%
where these energy patterns
furthermore are intrinsically

01:07:17.950 --> 01:07:22.390 align:middle line:84%
dynamic, the whole universe
being some sort of a cosmic

01:07:22.390 --> 01:07:24.250 align:middle line:90%
dance of energy.

01:07:24.250 --> 01:07:28.790 align:middle line:84%
Stan was describing very
similar experiences.

01:07:28.790 --> 01:07:31.990 align:middle line:84%
And as I did, he
was comparing them

01:07:31.990 --> 01:07:34.510 align:middle line:90%
to the experience of mystics.

01:07:34.510 --> 01:07:37.240 align:middle line:90%
Now we had three perspectives.

01:07:37.240 --> 01:07:40.960 align:middle line:84%
The mystical experience, the
transpersonal experience,

01:07:40.960 --> 01:07:45.130 align:middle line:84%
and the experience of physicists
in those subatomic experiments.

01:07:45.130 --> 01:07:48.190 align:middle line:84%
>> After lunch when people
came, it was time for me to talk

01:07:48.190 --> 01:07:49.930 align:middle line:90%
about my research.

01:07:49.930 --> 01:07:54.165 align:middle line:10%
It was pretty sober as compared
to what Fritjof was describing.

01:07:54.165 --> 01:07:55.540 align:middle line:10%
And I was talking
about something

01:07:55.540 --> 01:07:58.060 align:middle line:10%
that happens in some unusual
states of consciousness,

01:07:58.060 --> 01:08:00.820 align:middle line:10%
whereas Fritjof was
redefining the material

01:08:00.820 --> 01:08:02.380 align:middle line:10%
world that we live in.

01:08:02.380 --> 01:08:05.260 align:middle line:10%
>> One of the key insights from
the new physics is that reality

01:08:05.260 --> 01:08:08.810 align:middle line:10%
has something of a holographic
structure or a fractal

01:08:08.810 --> 01:08:09.610 align:middle line:10%
structure.

01:08:09.610 --> 01:08:13.570 align:middle line:84%
And the simplest example of
this is a mathematical structure

01:08:13.570 --> 01:08:15.910 align:middle line:90%
that we call the Mandelbrot set.

01:08:15.910 --> 01:08:18.880 align:middle line:84%
Now in science, this
is called nested sets

01:08:18.880 --> 01:08:22.210 align:middle line:84%
of self-similar
structures, but I

01:08:22.210 --> 01:08:24.399 align:middle line:84%
like to think that
this is actually

01:08:24.399 --> 01:08:29.050 align:middle line:84%
a modern scientific discovery
of an ancient hermetic principle

01:08:29.050 --> 01:08:29.950 align:middle line:90%
of alchemy.

01:08:29.950 --> 01:08:32.229 align:middle line:90%
As above, so below.

01:08:32.229 --> 01:08:34.569 align:middle line:90%
As within, so without.

01:08:34.569 --> 01:08:40.000 align:middle line:84%
That basically, the microcosm
replicates the macrocosm.

01:08:40.000 --> 01:08:43.240 align:middle line:84%
If we apply these
ideas to spirituality,

01:08:43.240 --> 01:08:46.479 align:middle line:84%
what I would propose
is that consciousness

01:08:46.479 --> 01:08:50.170 align:middle line:84%
itself has the same
fractal structure, which

01:08:50.170 --> 01:08:52.689 align:middle line:84%
means that there is
a self-similarity

01:08:52.689 --> 01:08:55.859 align:middle line:90%
at all levels of existence.

01:08:55.859 --> 01:09:01.859 align:middle line:84%
>> Stan was one of the
very first to give this new

01:09:01.859 --> 01:09:06.210 align:middle line:84%
conception of life and this
new perception of reality

01:09:06.210 --> 01:09:09.930 align:middle line:84%
an emotional content,
an experiential content.

01:09:09.930 --> 01:09:14.609 align:middle line:84%
I think this is one of his
many great contributions.

01:09:14.609 --> 01:09:17.580 align:middle line:10%
>> So many new perspectives
were introduced during those

01:09:17.580 --> 01:09:19.979 align:middle line:10%
workshops and
month-long intensives.

01:09:19.979 --> 01:09:22.680 align:middle line:10%
Michael Harner, who Stan
had met on his first trip

01:09:22.680 --> 01:09:24.990 align:middle line:10%
to the United States,
presented his work

01:09:24.990 --> 01:09:27.479 align:middle line:10%
in core shamanic practices.

01:09:27.479 --> 01:09:28.840 align:middle line:90%
>> It was 1965.

01:09:28.840 --> 01:09:30.420 align:middle line:90%
We met at the Esalen bathtubs.

01:09:30.420 --> 01:09:32.640 align:middle line:90%
Is that--

01:09:32.640 --> 01:09:35.570 align:middle line:84%
>> Yes, this was an
interesting meeting.

01:09:35.570 --> 01:09:38.855 align:middle line:84%
We were both stark
naked when we first met.

01:09:38.855 --> 01:09:39.655 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah.

01:09:39.655 --> 01:09:42.960 align:middle line:90%
A good way to start.

01:09:42.960 --> 01:09:45.060 align:middle line:90%
Had nothing to hide.

01:09:45.060 --> 01:09:47.040 align:middle line:84%
>> Richard Tarnas,
together with Stan,

01:09:47.040 --> 01:09:50.609 align:middle line:84%
developed archetypal astrology
as a means for gaining a deeper

01:09:50.609 --> 01:09:53.729 align:middle line:84%
understanding of the forces
influencing individual

01:09:53.729 --> 01:09:56.080 align:middle line:90%
and collective psyches.

01:09:56.080 --> 01:10:00.340 align:middle line:84%
>> We noticed the phenomenology
of the perinatal matrices could

01:10:00.340 --> 01:10:04.030 align:middle line:84%
have been passages from
handbooks of astrology.

01:10:04.030 --> 01:10:05.740 align:middle line:84%
So that was mind
blowing, because I

01:10:05.740 --> 01:10:09.410 align:middle line:84%
had no understanding of
astrology when I was doing it.

01:10:09.410 --> 01:10:11.830 align:middle line:84%
But then we found out
something even more amazing,

01:10:11.830 --> 01:10:14.710 align:middle line:84%
that actually people were
having in their sessions

01:10:14.710 --> 01:10:17.950 align:middle line:84%
the encounter with elements of
these matrices at the time when

01:10:17.950 --> 01:10:21.820 align:middle line:84%
they had these planets as
some significant transit.

01:10:21.820 --> 01:10:25.360 align:middle line:10%
So it became
something that allowed

01:10:25.360 --> 01:10:29.040 align:middle line:10%
prediction, what kind of
experiences people would have.

01:10:29.040 --> 01:10:32.910 align:middle line:10%
I had the chance to spend
very informal time with people

01:10:32.910 --> 01:10:34.920 align:middle line:10%
who were the pioneers.

01:10:34.920 --> 01:10:38.310 align:middle line:84%
You know, Fritjof Capra,
Rupert Sheldrake, Karl Pribram.

01:10:38.310 --> 01:10:40.935 align:middle line:84%
We had Huston Smith,
Joseph Campbell.

01:10:40.935 --> 01:10:45.010 align:middle line:84%
No university had
that kind of a staff.

01:10:45.010 --> 01:10:47.760 align:middle line:10%
So when I started the
International Transpersonal

01:10:47.760 --> 01:10:50.280 align:middle line:10%
Association, I could
pick up the telephone

01:10:50.280 --> 01:10:53.940 align:middle line:10%
and say, I want to do a
conference in Bombay, in India.

01:10:53.940 --> 01:10:57.180 align:middle line:84%
I can pay the round-trip
ticket and feed you.

01:10:57.180 --> 01:10:58.440 align:middle line:90%
They put you up.

01:10:58.440 --> 01:11:01.050 align:middle line:90%
But I can't give any honorarium.

01:11:01.050 --> 01:11:01.890 align:middle line:90%
Do you want to come?

01:11:01.890 --> 01:11:04.440 align:middle line:90%
And they all said yes.

01:11:04.440 --> 01:11:07.530 align:middle line:84%
>> Stan Grof wrote me a long
handwritten letter saying how

01:11:07.530 --> 01:11:08.850 align:middle line:90%
much he liked my book.

01:11:08.850 --> 01:11:10.320 align:middle line:90%
He'd had a copy shipped.

01:11:10.320 --> 01:11:12.960 align:middle line:84%
And he invited me to
speak at a conference

01:11:12.960 --> 01:11:15.080 align:middle line:90%
he was organizing in Bombay.

01:11:15.080 --> 01:11:16.455 align:middle line:84%
But I'd never been
to California,

01:11:16.455 --> 01:11:19.620 align:middle line:84%
and I'd never heard of things
like the New Age movement.

01:11:19.620 --> 01:11:21.030 align:middle line:90%
I'd never heard of Stan Grof.

01:11:21.030 --> 01:11:22.620 align:middle line:90%
I'd never heard of Esalen.

01:11:22.620 --> 01:11:25.380 align:middle line:84%
And suddenly in this
hotel it was a kind

01:11:25.380 --> 01:11:27.360 align:middle line:84%
of astonishing
world of people who

01:11:27.360 --> 01:11:28.980 align:middle line:84%
were into
consciousness research,

01:11:28.980 --> 01:11:31.230 align:middle line:84%
talking about the
Esalen Institute.

01:11:31.230 --> 01:11:35.640 align:middle line:84%
Stan was talking about his
psychotropic breathing and LSD

01:11:35.640 --> 01:11:37.560 align:middle line:90%
research, and so on.

01:11:37.560 --> 01:11:39.960 align:middle line:84%
I was amazed to find
myself in an environment

01:11:39.960 --> 01:11:41.430 align:middle line:84%
where I could talk
about the things

01:11:41.430 --> 01:11:43.200 align:middle line:84%
I was really most
interested in, where

01:11:43.200 --> 01:11:46.200 align:middle line:84%
people were interested
in finding out

01:11:46.200 --> 01:11:49.530 align:middle line:84%
more, a kind of fizz of
excitement and discovery

01:11:49.530 --> 01:11:52.050 align:middle line:90%
and new horizons.

01:11:52.050 --> 01:11:55.260 align:middle line:84%
>> People were just very hungry
to find an atmosphere where

01:11:55.260 --> 01:11:57.540 align:middle line:84%
they could connect with
like-minded people.

01:11:57.540 --> 01:11:59.580 align:middle line:84%
They were not
afraid of criticism

01:11:59.580 --> 01:12:02.580 align:middle line:84%
that would have any implications
for their reputation

01:12:02.580 --> 01:12:04.440 align:middle line:90%
or their position.

01:12:04.440 --> 01:12:08.430 align:middle line:10%
So we really got the
truth from people.

01:12:08.430 --> 01:12:12.810 align:middle line:10%
>> There is a domain of
potentiality which is

01:12:12.810 --> 01:12:16.470 align:middle line:10%
non-local, and
therefore, it is oneness.

01:12:16.470 --> 01:12:18.240 align:middle line:84%
>> The universe
doesn't work on the--

01:12:18.240 --> 01:12:22.920 align:middle line:84%
>> Stan represents what
has been sorely lacking,

01:12:22.920 --> 01:12:28.180 align:middle line:84%
which is the long throughline,
a work over decades.

01:12:28.180 --> 01:12:33.850 align:middle line:84%
Because in this wild,
meandering exploration

01:12:33.850 --> 01:12:36.440 align:middle line:84%
of the further reaches
of human nature,

01:12:36.440 --> 01:12:39.820 align:middle line:84%
particularly in the '60s, but
even in the long sobering up

01:12:39.820 --> 01:12:42.940 align:middle line:84%
of the '70s, he's
been able to provide

01:12:42.940 --> 01:12:46.870 align:middle line:90%
a huge body of empirical lore.

01:12:46.870 --> 01:12:50.320 align:middle line:10%
>> It's fair to say, I think,
that I wouldn't be doing

01:12:50.320 --> 01:12:54.310 align:middle line:10%
the research that I'm doing had
it not have been for reading

01:12:54.310 --> 01:12:57.550 align:middle line:10%
Stan's "Realms of the
Human Unconscious."

01:12:57.550 --> 01:13:00.250 align:middle line:10%
>> Yet despite the tremendous
insights shared during

01:13:00.250 --> 01:13:03.520 align:middle line:10%
Stan's tenure at Esalen and
his continued exploration

01:13:03.520 --> 01:13:05.800 align:middle line:10%
of the healing power
of non-ordinary states

01:13:05.800 --> 01:13:09.320 align:middle line:10%
of consciousness, so
little has changed.

01:13:09.320 --> 01:13:12.300 align:middle line:84%
>> The work with holotropic
states also provides very,

01:13:12.300 --> 01:13:16.910 align:middle line:84%
very interesting insight
into how we should approach

01:13:16.910 --> 01:13:20.570 align:middle line:84%
the situation that we have
in the world where we are

01:13:20.570 --> 01:13:24.070 align:middle line:84%
in global crisis, in some
sense on the verge of possible

01:13:24.070 --> 01:13:24.870 align:middle line:90%
extinction.

01:13:24.870 --> 01:13:30.290 align:middle line:10%
And not just our species, but
taking a few species with us.

01:13:30.290 --> 01:13:32.720 align:middle line:84%
Changing the situation
is not simple.

01:13:32.720 --> 01:13:36.920 align:middle line:84%
We cannot just do
kind of transpersonal,

01:13:36.920 --> 01:13:39.350 align:middle line:84%
spiritual sanitization
of creation,

01:13:39.350 --> 01:13:42.650 align:middle line:84%
if we simply eliminate
everything that we don't like

01:13:42.650 --> 01:13:46.850 align:middle line:90%
that we think is bad or evil.

01:13:46.850 --> 01:13:49.580 align:middle line:84%
>> It was hard for me to
hear what Stan was saying.

01:13:49.580 --> 01:13:53.210 align:middle line:84%
I'd always hoped that one
could avoid darkness and pain.

01:13:53.210 --> 01:13:55.940 align:middle line:84%
I didn't want to believe
that light and shadow were

01:13:55.940 --> 01:13:59.150 align:middle line:90%
equal parts of the whole.

01:13:59.150 --> 01:14:01.580 align:middle line:84%
Perhaps ayahuasca could help
me make peace with that.

01:14:01.580 --> 01:14:05.250 align:middle line:90%


01:14:05.250 --> 01:14:07.190 align:middle line:84%
The problem with
ayahuasca is that it can

01:14:07.190 --> 01:14:09.650 align:middle line:90%
take a long time to come on.

01:14:09.650 --> 01:14:12.710 align:middle line:84%
The mistake that I made was
thinking I hadn't had enough.

01:14:12.710 --> 01:14:18.030 align:middle line:90%


01:14:18.030 --> 01:14:21.360 align:middle line:90%
I really thought I was dying.

01:14:21.360 --> 01:14:25.110 align:middle line:84%
But in my heart, I knew
that it was too late.

01:14:25.110 --> 01:14:29.540 align:middle line:84%
There was nothing to be done,
so I purged and surrendered.

01:14:29.540 --> 01:14:35.650 align:middle line:90%


01:14:35.650 --> 01:14:37.480 align:middle line:84%
It took me a while
to realize that I

01:14:37.480 --> 01:14:40.480 align:middle line:84%
was in another dimension, and
that as long as I remained

01:14:40.480 --> 01:14:42.940 align:middle line:90%
formless in it, I was fine.

01:14:42.940 --> 01:14:47.050 align:middle line:84%
If I tried to feel my body,
I was instantly nauseous.

01:14:47.050 --> 01:14:50.650 align:middle line:84%
For six hours, I stayed
in the quantum field.

01:14:50.650 --> 01:14:54.700 align:middle line:84%
At times, it seemed I was
watching reincarnation

01:14:54.700 --> 01:14:57.610 align:middle line:84%
where a soul would merge
with the possibility wave

01:14:57.610 --> 01:15:01.690 align:middle line:84%
and then tumble down into
increasing density, flipping

01:15:01.690 --> 01:15:07.230 align:middle line:84%
like a coin between
victim and perpetrator.

01:15:07.230 --> 01:15:08.970 align:middle line:84%
Pretty much every
deep experience

01:15:08.970 --> 01:15:11.670 align:middle line:84%
I've had since has been
uncomfortable in ways

01:15:11.670 --> 01:15:14.280 align:middle line:90%
I never could have imagined.

01:15:14.280 --> 01:15:18.210 align:middle line:84%
But most often, I end up in a
place of great beauty and love,

01:15:18.210 --> 01:15:22.080 align:middle line:84%
as though the ugliness had to be
fully experienced before I had

01:15:22.080 --> 01:15:25.230 align:middle line:90%
access to the underlying joy.

01:15:25.230 --> 01:15:27.960 align:middle line:84%
When I look back at my
archetypal astrology,

01:15:27.960 --> 01:15:32.640 align:middle line:84%
I see now that I've been through
a series of death and rebirth.

01:15:32.640 --> 01:15:35.820 align:middle line:84%
What died was my
limited sense of self.

01:15:35.820 --> 01:15:38.100 align:middle line:84%
Once that illusion
slipped away, I

01:15:38.100 --> 01:15:41.040 align:middle line:84%
could feel my true
nature as energy

01:15:41.040 --> 01:15:43.440 align:middle line:84%
beyond the creative
and destructive cycles

01:15:43.440 --> 01:15:46.380 align:middle line:84%
of the universe,
timeless and vast,

01:15:46.380 --> 01:15:50.160 align:middle line:84%
within a unity that might
be forgotten but never lost.

01:15:50.160 --> 01:15:53.510 align:middle line:90%


01:15:53.510 --> 01:15:55.970 align:middle line:10%
>> I think it's healthier
to know that the devil is

01:15:55.970 --> 01:15:59.930 align:middle line:10%
something within our psyches
and within our souls as humans

01:15:59.930 --> 01:16:06.490 align:middle line:10%
rather than some
object out there.

01:16:06.490 --> 01:16:10.030 align:middle line:84%
>> I think people who are
in touch with the state

01:16:10.030 --> 01:16:13.510 align:middle line:84%
of the world right now recognize
that we're basically all

01:16:13.510 --> 01:16:14.920 align:middle line:90%
skating on thin ice.

01:16:14.920 --> 01:16:18.550 align:middle line:84%
There is a profound
sense of uncertainty

01:16:18.550 --> 01:16:23.980 align:middle line:84%
and potentially looming danger
of catastrophic proportions.

01:16:23.980 --> 01:16:26.620 align:middle line:84%
And it takes a lot of
courage to face that.

01:16:26.620 --> 01:16:29.380 align:middle line:84%
We can't simply be
sure we can be bringing

01:16:29.380 --> 01:16:32.560 align:middle line:84%
in some technological fix
or a rational solution

01:16:32.560 --> 01:16:33.970 align:middle line:90%
to this situation.

01:16:33.970 --> 01:16:37.600 align:middle line:84%
Uncertainty itself
is a key part of

01:16:37.600 --> 01:16:40.340 align:middle line:90%
any initiatory transformation.

01:16:40.340 --> 01:16:43.510 align:middle line:84%
You can't have a pretend
near-death experience

01:16:43.510 --> 01:16:47.680 align:middle line:84%
in order to have an effective
transfiguration of how

01:16:47.680 --> 01:16:48.560 align:middle line:90%
you live.

01:16:48.560 --> 01:16:51.400 align:middle line:84%
You need to really feel
everything is at stake

01:16:51.400 --> 01:16:53.690 align:middle line:90%
and you don't know the outcome.

01:16:53.690 --> 01:16:56.500 align:middle line:84%
And if we can have the
courage to face that

01:16:56.500 --> 01:16:59.290 align:middle line:84%
and to go through this
dark night of the soul,

01:16:59.290 --> 01:17:02.680 align:middle line:84%
in some sense, and to bring
all our' wits and heart

01:17:02.680 --> 01:17:06.010 align:middle line:84%
and imagination and
bravery together

01:17:06.010 --> 01:17:08.620 align:middle line:84%
to engage this
great threshold, I

01:17:08.620 --> 01:17:13.030 align:middle line:84%
think that's the
key to our future.

01:17:13.030 --> 01:17:14.470 align:middle line:84%
>> If anybody's
paying attention,

01:17:14.470 --> 01:17:16.570 align:middle line:90%
they're traumatized in some way.

01:17:16.570 --> 01:17:20.410 align:middle line:84%
And psychedelics can help
us deal with those fears

01:17:20.410 --> 01:17:22.930 align:middle line:84%
and still look
positively at what

01:17:22.930 --> 01:17:24.770 align:middle line:84%
we can do to contribute
to make them better.

01:17:24.770 --> 01:17:26.770 align:middle line:84%
So there's a lot of
the astronauts who've

01:17:26.770 --> 01:17:28.600 align:middle line:84%
looked back at the
Earth from space

01:17:28.600 --> 01:17:32.710 align:middle line:84%
and realized that it's a
single organism, that there

01:17:32.710 --> 01:17:35.090 align:middle line:84%
are no clear country boundaries,
that we're all in this

01:17:35.090 --> 01:17:35.890 align:middle line:90%
together.

01:17:35.890 --> 01:17:38.680 align:middle line:84%
We're all part of this 14
billion years of evolution

01:17:38.680 --> 01:17:40.570 align:middle line:90%
and have been spiritualized.

01:17:40.570 --> 01:17:43.870 align:middle line:84%
When people grasp the
sense of the whole,

01:17:43.870 --> 01:17:45.712 align:middle line:84%
that has profound
political implications.

01:17:45.712 --> 01:17:47.920 align:middle line:84%
And it's a lot cheaper to
give somebody a psychedelic

01:17:47.920 --> 01:17:49.212 align:middle line:90%
than shoot them up to the moon.

01:17:49.212 --> 01:17:52.720 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHS]

01:17:52.720 --> 01:17:55.840 align:middle line:84%
>> The power of psychedelics
to profoundly change people is

01:17:55.840 --> 01:17:56.640 align:middle line:90%
remarkable.

01:17:56.640 --> 01:17:59.390 align:middle line:90%


01:17:59.390 --> 01:18:03.580 align:middle line:84%
>> The information that was
delivered to me in those

01:18:03.580 --> 01:18:08.410 align:middle line:84%
experiences has pretty much
formed the rest of my life

01:18:08.410 --> 01:18:09.670 align:middle line:90%
since then.

01:18:09.670 --> 01:18:11.850 align:middle line:90%
>> The depression was gone.

01:18:11.850 --> 01:18:15.160 align:middle line:90%
Never came back.

01:18:15.160 --> 01:18:20.120 align:middle line:84%
I became a different
person who was

01:18:20.120 --> 01:18:25.280 align:middle line:84%
able to enjoy life,
learn how to love,

01:18:25.280 --> 01:18:29.060 align:middle line:84%
who was nicer to my children
and my grandchildren.

01:18:29.060 --> 01:18:32.360 align:middle line:84%
The substance, which
was a psychedelic,

01:18:32.360 --> 01:18:35.990 align:middle line:84%
helped me so much
that I dedicated

01:18:35.990 --> 01:18:41.780 align:middle line:84%
the rest of my life to make
it available to everyone

01:18:41.780 --> 01:18:43.410 align:middle line:90%
who suffers.

01:18:43.410 --> 01:18:46.980 align:middle line:84%
>> I now have
completely, 180 degrees,

01:18:46.980 --> 01:18:50.880 align:middle line:84%
modified my viewpoint to
understand that we are

01:18:50.880 --> 01:18:56.100 align:middle line:84%
spiritual beings, performing and
acting and learning in physical

01:18:56.100 --> 01:18:57.160 align:middle line:90%
bodies.

01:18:57.160 --> 01:18:59.610 align:middle line:84%
And it is through the power
of some of the psychedelics,

01:18:59.610 --> 01:19:02.310 align:middle line:84%
it's through some of the
ideas of Stan and the people

01:19:02.310 --> 01:19:05.760 align:middle line:84%
that he has brought together
with him that this new opening

01:19:05.760 --> 01:19:10.560 align:middle line:84%
has happened in my life as well
as in the lives of thousands

01:19:10.560 --> 01:19:12.420 align:middle line:90%
and millions of people.

01:19:12.420 --> 01:19:16.740 align:middle line:84%
>> And now ever since that,
any time when things like this

01:19:16.740 --> 01:19:19.500 align:middle line:84%
happen-- of course, they
happen again and again--

01:19:19.500 --> 01:19:22.350 align:middle line:90%
I remember what Stan told me.

01:19:22.350 --> 01:19:24.180 align:middle line:90%
You're ready.

01:19:24.180 --> 01:19:25.980 align:middle line:90%
Face it.

01:19:25.980 --> 01:19:29.620 align:middle line:84%
Your psyche will not give
you any task that you cannot

01:19:29.620 --> 01:19:30.420 align:middle line:90%
tackle.

01:19:30.420 --> 01:19:33.050 align:middle line:90%


01:19:33.050 --> 01:19:36.050 align:middle line:10%
>> Regardless of the method,
it's the state one finds

01:19:36.050 --> 01:19:39.710 align:middle line:10%
themselves in that
matters, awake and joyful

01:19:39.710 --> 01:19:42.800 align:middle line:10%
in the heartfelt knowledge
of being part of something

01:19:42.800 --> 01:19:45.510 align:middle line:10%
greater.

01:19:45.510 --> 01:19:48.360 align:middle line:84%
It's only fitting that Stan
experienced his own rebirth

01:19:48.360 --> 01:19:50.280 align:middle line:90%
after Christina's passing.

01:19:50.280 --> 01:19:53.010 align:middle line:84%
For years, he had suffered
from debilitating back

01:19:53.010 --> 01:19:55.950 align:middle line:84%
pain and nerve
sensitivity in his legs,

01:19:55.950 --> 01:19:58.830 align:middle line:84%
but a higher than normal
dose of medical marijuana

01:19:58.830 --> 01:20:02.370 align:middle line:84%
launched a process that
freed him from that pain.

01:20:02.370 --> 01:20:05.460 align:middle line:84%
>> And I had the feeling
that I was dying.

01:20:05.460 --> 01:20:09.000 align:middle line:84%
And I saw all the people
who died before me--

01:20:09.000 --> 01:20:12.570 align:middle line:84%
Angie Arrien and
Christina, Sasha Shulgin

01:20:12.570 --> 01:20:14.790 align:middle line:90%
and Hans Ruedi Giger.

01:20:14.790 --> 01:20:16.890 align:middle line:84%
So I had the feeling this
is the end of an era,

01:20:16.890 --> 01:20:18.660 align:middle line:90%
and I was joining.

01:20:18.660 --> 01:20:22.720 align:middle line:84%
And then there was that sense
like, no, you're not ready yet.

01:20:22.720 --> 01:20:24.630 align:middle line:84%
And sort of, you
go back, you know?

01:20:24.630 --> 01:20:26.260 align:middle line:90%
You have more work to do.

01:20:26.260 --> 01:20:29.070 align:middle line:84%
And I went for about
a month into a lot

01:20:29.070 --> 01:20:31.420 align:middle line:84%
of non-ordinary states
of consciousness.

01:20:31.420 --> 01:20:33.790 align:middle line:90%
Spontaneous chanting was coming.

01:20:33.790 --> 01:20:37.890 align:middle line:84%
A significant part of
it was about whales.

01:20:37.890 --> 01:20:41.340 align:middle line:84%
>> During this period, Brigitte,
one of Stan's first students

01:20:41.340 --> 01:20:44.670 align:middle line:84%
and dearly loved by
him, reached out.

01:20:44.670 --> 01:20:48.060 align:middle line:10%
